这是绝对不能发生的。

300
00:23:24,359 --> 00:23:27,160
Well, look, I don't feel
comfortable getting into the middle of something.
好吧，听着，我不太愿意掺和进来。

301
00:23:27,200 --> 00:23:29,400
Do you think you're gonna be a leading man forever?
你觉得，你会永远是男主角吗?

302
00:23:30,079 --> 00:23:34,920
You need to face the facts, son.
This war took the best years of your life.
你得面对现实，孩子。这场战争，夺走了你最美好的年华。

303
00:23:35,519 --> 00:23:40,319
You got, what, five years of smiling for
the camera until they put you out to pasture?
你有五年对着镜头微笑，直到他们把你赶出去吗?

304
00:23:40,559 --> 00:23:42,000
Thanks for the pep talk, Jack.
谢谢你的鼓励，杰克。

305
00:23:42,219 --> 00:23:43,219
War.
战争

306
00:23:44,700 --> 00:23:47,120
Do you make a difference?
你能来一次改变吗?

307
00:23:49,860 --> 00:23:50,939
A real difference.
一次真正的改变。

308
00:23:57,200 --> 00:24:02,039
[SIGHS]
[叹息]

309
00:24:13,039 --> 00:24:20,400
The movies are a platform that we as
actors are proud and privileged to be a part of.
电影是一个平台，我们作为演员，很自豪也很荣幸能参与其中。
（演员公会年会）

310
00:24:21,480 --> 00:24:25,119
We are the face in the lifeblood of American movies.
我们是美国电影的命脉。

311
00:24:26,200 --> 00:24:31,520
And so we must be vigilant and make
ourselves aware of others they may seek to use
所以我们必须保持警惕，让自己意识到，其他人可能会

312
00:24:31,620 --> 00:24:35,899
our platform to use us for their own purposes.
利用我们的平台，来利用我们，达到他们自己的目的。

313
00:24:56,200 --> 00:24:58,359
[MUSIC PLAYING]
[音乐奏起]

314
00:24:59,900 --> 00:25:01,940
Was it something I said?
我说的有什么不妥吗？

315
00:25:02,759 --> 00:25:07,799
I'm just curious.Maybe an actor or a politician.
我只是好奇。你到底是演员，还是政治家。

316
00:25:08,119 --> 00:25:11,120
Jane, not here. Not now. Please.
简，在这儿不要吵，现在不要吵。求你了。

317
00:25:11,640 --> 00:25:15,400
If you put as much work into your career as you do
如果你在事业上投入的精力，和你在演讲上

318
00:25:15,500 --> 00:25:18,819
making your speeches, you'd have an Oscar by now.
投入的精力一样多，你早就拿上奥斯卡奖了。

319
00:25:19,039 --> 00:25:22,440
Jane, this is Zach. This is our union.
简，这是扎克。这是我们的联盟。

320
00:25:23,440 --> 00:25:27,240
And a big vice president of screen
actors killed us like a gift from God. I really
一个负责影视演员的大副总裁，会像上帝赐予的礼物一样，扼杀了我们。

321
00:25:27,340 --> 00:25:30,759
feel like I can do something that matters here.
我真的觉得，我能在这里，做些有意义的事。

322
00:25:31,340 --> 00:25:35,160
Was there anything worse than an actor with a cause?
还有什么，比耽误一个有事业的演员，更糟糕的吗?

323
00:25:37,960 --> 00:25:42,059
Kill your career if you must,
Ronnie, but spare me your damn speeches.
如果有必要，就毁了你的事业，罗尼，但别再让我听，你这破演讲了。

324
00:25:43,599 --> 00:25:48,759
You are an actor.That is your job. Not politics.
你是个演员。那是你的工作。而非政治。

325
00:26:22,559 --> 00:26:25,559
（演员公会办公室
加州，好莱坞）

326
00:26:25,759 --> 00:26:29,939
No. What do you mean no? Higher
wages, better working conditions. That's what we
不。你说不，是什么意思？更高的工资，更好的工作条件。这是我们都想要的。

327
00:26:30,039 --> 00:26:31,820
all want. That's what we're all going for.
这就是我们所追求的。

328
00:26:31,920 --> 00:26:36,200
You want to shut it all down. What is it that you really want?
你想把这一切都关掉。你到底想要什么?

329
00:26:36,559 --> 00:26:40,720
One union and unite it. Look,
you don't want to go to war with us, Reagan.
组成一个工会，把它团结起来。听着，你不会想和我们开战的，里根。

330
00:26:42,200 --> 00:26:50,960
But what nobody knew was that Reagan
was an FBI informant. His code name T-10.
但没人知道，里根是联邦调查局的线人。他的代号是T-10。

331
00:26:51,519 --> 00:26:55,599
And he was exposing a growing influence in Hollywood.
他在好莱坞的影响力越来越大。
（好莱坞被证明：有共产势力渗入）

332
00:26:56,640 --> 00:27:01,160
Mr. Warner, can you provide the name of the leader of
the organization, the Tempe Team to infiltrate the studio?
华纳先生，你能提供潜入摄影棚的“坦佩小组”头目的名字吗?

333
00:27:02,920 --> 00:27:06,960
His name is Sorel. Herb Sorel.
他的名字叫索雷尔。赫伯.索雷尔。

334
00:27:07,800 --> 00:27:09,479
We're not joining you, Herb.
我们和你，不是一路的，赫伯。

335
00:27:17,899 --> 00:27:19,939
Put it down. It's okay.
-把枪放下。 -没事了。

336
00:27:22,519 --> 00:27:24,759
You don't get it,do you? We own this town.
你们不明白，是吗? 我们拥有这个小镇。

337
00:27:25,160 --> 00:27:27,279
You don't own me. You don't own them.
你没拥有我。你也没拥有他们。

338
00:27:28,839 --> 00:27:34,880
You want to take a vote right now, go ahead. Let's
put it to a vote. See what happens. See what happens.
你想现在投票，那就投吧。我们投票表决吧。看看会发生什么。会发生什么。

339
00:27:35,080 --> 00:27:38,080
（“演员公会”投票结果，继续保持独立地位。）

340
00:27:47,580 --> 00:27:48,980
（索雷尔在华纳兄弟影业公司的罢工引来骚乱）

341
00:27:49,039 --> 00:27:55,519
Mr. Hayden, in your opinion,
why weren't the communist efforts successful?
海登先生，在你看来，共产党的努力为什么没有成功?

342
00:27:56,900 --> 00:28:02,839
There was just one problem. They ran into the
board of directors of the Screen Actors Guild.
只有一个麻烦。他们遇到了美国“演员公工会”的理事会的领导。
（对立的各工会，在华纳制片厂群殴）

343
00:28:03,200 --> 00:28:08,799
In particular, Ronald Reagan was a one-man battalion against this thing.
特别是，罗纳德・里根，他是一个人反对这种事情的。
（前共产党员：斯特林.海登，后出演了《荒漠怪客》《奇爱博士》）

344
00:28:08,939 --> 00:28:09,980
Let's do a break.
让我们休息一下吧。

345
00:28:13,839 --> 00:28:19,640
As a citizen, I would not like to see any
political party outlawed on the basis of its ideology.
作为一名公民，我不希望看到任何政党，因其意识形态而被取缔。

346
00:28:20,519 --> 00:28:28,079
Democracy is strong enough to stand up for itself against the end
roads of any ideology, no matter how much we may disagree with it.
民主是强大到，足以站起来，反对任何意识形态的末路，无论我们多么不同意它。

347
00:28:28,200 --> 00:28:31,920
Because I still believe, Mr. Chairman, that democracy can handle it.
因为我仍然相信，主席先生，民主能够解决这个问题。

348
00:28:34,119 --> 00:28:43,640
He had shut us down. He was clever in his message that it
was okay to be communist,but not while being paid by us.
他挡了我们的路。他的狡猾信息表明:你可以是共产党，但不能拿我们的薪水。
（里根表态，反对苏联）

349
00:28:52,200 --> 00:28:54,519
And cut! That's lunch, everybody!
停拍！大家去吃午饭吧！

350
00:28:55,200 --> 00:28:59,160
You were great, didn't you? Sure. Let's grab the bucket.
你很棒，不是吗？ 当然。我们都“投篮得分”了。

351
00:28:59,420 --> 00:29:00,440
I'm here.
我来了。

352
00:29:01,400 --> 00:29:10,279
While his wife's career was skyrocketing, he was
reduced to sidelines,and their marriage deteriorated.
当他妻子的事业突飞猛进时，他却沦为旁观者，他们的婚姻也恶化了。

353
00:29:15,200 --> 00:29:23,279
And to break more his damaged heart, their third
child, Christine,died the very day she was born.
更让他伤心的是，他们的第三个孩子克里斯汀，在出生的那天，就去世了。

354
00:29:37,479 --> 00:29:40,679
（加利福尼亚州的圣费尔南多谷）

355
00:29:41,000 --> 00:29:42,419
How's my son?
儿子，你这是怎么了？

356
00:29:45,480 --> 00:29:51,920
I lost a child. Marriage, a career. How do you think your boy is?
我失去了一个孩子。婚姻，事业。你觉得，你儿子会怎么样？

357
00:29:53,940 --> 00:29:58,279
You know, Nellie,
I think I kind of missed the boat on that whole purpose thing.
你知道吗，内莉，我觉得，我几乎错过了达到人生目标的航船。

358
00:29:59,920 --> 00:30:02,440
Maybe I'll just jack all over again.
也许，我会再来一遍。

359
00:30:03,359 --> 00:30:05,559
No, Dutch. You're not your father.
不，“荷兰仔”。你不是你爹。

360
00:30:09,119 --> 00:30:18,160
Just remember to listen to that
small, soft voice, the one that you can't hear,
只要记住，去倾听那个微小而柔和的声音，那个你听不到的声音，

361
00:30:19,279 --> 00:30:26,960
unless you're alone and quiet, and he has your full attention.
除非你独自一人，安静地，而他 会占据了你全部的注意力。

362
00:30:29,960 --> 00:30:35,039
Remember who you are, and whom you serve.
你要记住，你是谁，你为谁服务。

363
00:30:47,040 --> 00:30:48,300
Yes, Sandy?
什么事，桑蒂？

364
00:30:49,239 --> 00:30:51,379
Can you give an actress five minutes?
你能和这位女演员，谈五分钟吗？

365
00:30:52,440 --> 00:30:53,640
Of course.
当然可以。

366
00:30:54,059 --> 00:30:55,259
Miss Davis?
戴维斯小姐？

367
00:30:55,700 --> 00:30:57,740
Hello. I'm Nancy Davis.
你好。我是南希.戴维斯。

368
00:30:57,840 --> 00:30:59,759
Hello, Nancy Davis. I'm Ron Reagan.
你好，南希.戴维斯。我就是罗恩.里根。

369
00:31:00,000 --> 00:31:01,219
Yes, I know.
是的，我知道。

370
00:31:01,600 --> 00:31:03,039
How about a cup of coffee?
来杯咖啡怎么样？

371
00:31:03,219 --> 00:31:04,220
Oh, sure.
哦，当然可以。

372
00:31:04,319 --> 00:31:05,399
Have a seat.
请坐。

373
00:31:06,839 --> 00:31:11,359
I'm afraid I've been a pest to your
secretary, but I persist when it's important.
恐怕，我一直让你的秘书很讨厌，但我是“无事不登三宝殿”。

374
00:31:11,879 --> 00:31:13,159
Cream, sugar?
加奶油，还是加方糖？

375
00:31:13,359 --> 00:31:15,000
Oh, well, sure. I'm black.
都可以。还是纯咖啡吧。

376
00:31:15,400 --> 00:31:21,319
Oh. Well, how can I help you, Nancy Davis?
哦。我能帮你什么忙吗，南希・戴维斯？

377
00:31:22,599 --> 00:31:31,440
Well, I'm listed as a signer on a letter of support for two
communist sympathizers, but I never signed any such letter.
一封支持两名“共产主义同情者”的信上，有我的签名，但我从来未签过这样的名。

378
00:31:31,700 --> 00:31:33,340
There's another Nancy Davis.
还有另一个叫同样名的“南茜.戴维斯”。

379
00:31:33,720 --> 00:31:39,799
Oh, I see. Well, the easiest thing to do is just
change your name, and it happens all the time in Hollywood.
哦，我明白了。最简单的办法就是改名字，这在好莱坞屡见不鲜。

380
00:31:40,039 --> 00:31:46,880
Oh, no. No, I cannot do that. No. My
name is very important to me. It's my family.
哦，不。不，我不能那样做。不。我的名字对我来说很重要。这是我的家人。

381
00:31:47,240 --> 00:31:49,880
Oh, of course. And family's important.
哦，当然。家庭很重要。

382
00:31:50,919 --> 00:31:51,919
Yes.
是的。

383
00:31:52,559 --> 00:31:53,559
Very important.
非常重要。

384
00:31:56,480 --> 00:32:02,500
So, I guess there's only one thing left to do, and that
is to launch an exhaustive and detailed investigation.
所以，我想我们只剩下一件事要做了，那就是展开一次详尽的调查。

385
00:32:02,919 --> 00:32:05,020
Well, of course,I've retained an attorney.
当然了，我已经邀约了一位律师。

386
00:32:05,319 --> 00:32:08,079
Oh, there won't be any need for that.
We can knock this out over dinner.
哦，那就没必要了。我们可以边吃晚餐边聊。

387
00:32:08,199 --> 00:32:09,279
Excuse me?
对不起？

388
00:32:09,500 --> 00:32:16,160
Yes. We can discuss it then, but I can't be late. I,
yes. I have a movie studio called tomorrow morning.
那我们到时候再谈吧，但我不能迟到，正好明早，有个摄影棚打电话约我拍戏。

389
00:32:16,440 --> 00:32:19,200
Oh, well, I'll have to check my date book.
哦，好吧，我得查一下我的记事本。

390
00:32:21,200 --> 00:32:22,380
Goodie.
全靠这个了。

391
00:32:22,660 --> 00:32:23,660
Yes.
好的。

392
00:32:23,939 --> 00:32:25,680
Yes. Um...
是的。嗯...

393
00:32:28,160 --> 00:32:32,680
Well, well, I think I can manage it, but I have an early call too.
好吧，好吧，我想我能应付得来，但我也要早起，开工拍戏。

394
00:32:32,979 --> 00:32:34,240
Well, then it's a date.
好吧，那就定下来吧。

395
00:32:34,499 --> 00:32:36,139
Yes. Okay.
好的。没问题。

396
00:32:36,399 --> 00:32:37,399
Okay.
好的。

397
00:32:39,200 --> 00:32:40,920
Goodbye for now.
那就再见了。

398
00:32:45,200 --> 00:32:46,200
Goodbye, Taylor.
再见，泰勒。

399
00:32:52,039 --> 00:32:54,279
Okay, Poppy. Thanks.I'm gonna take care of that.
好的,波比。谢谢。我会点菜的。

400
00:33:06,040 --> 00:33:08,279
Well, it looks like we've shut the place down.
看来，我们一来，把这地方的生意给“搅黄”了。

401
00:33:08,599 --> 00:33:10,460
Yes, we did here.
好的，我们就在这儿谈吧。

402
00:33:18,000 --> 00:33:20,039
Thank you, Joseph.
谢谢你，约瑟夫。

403
00:33:21,319 --> 00:33:26,599
Miss Davis, I'm gonna get on this first thing in
the morning, and I'll make all the calls myself.
戴维斯小姐，我明天一早就去办这件事，所有的电话，都由我来打。

404
00:33:26,919 --> 00:33:29,959
Your name will be off that list.
你的名字，将会从那名单中去除。

405
00:33:30,200 --> 00:33:32,160
-Just like that.-Just like that.
-那么简单。  -就像这样。

406
00:33:32,200 --> 00:33:40,880
So, um, when you're not acting or being SAG president,
what do you like to do with your time, Mr. Reagan?
那么，当你不演戏或不做“演员公会”主席的时候，你喜欢做什么呢，里根先生?

407
00:33:41,880 --> 00:33:43,920
I like the outdoors.
我喜欢户外运动。

408
00:33:44,200 --> 00:33:45,039
Mm-hmm.
嗯，嗯。

409
00:33:45,440 --> 00:33:46,699
I play golf.
我喜欢打高尔夫。

410
00:33:47,960 --> 00:33:50,480
And I love riding horses.
我还喜欢骑马。

411
00:33:50,760 --> 00:33:51,800
No.
不会吧。

412
00:33:51,840 --> 00:33:52,859
Yes. Do you ride?
是的。你喜欢骑马？

413
00:33:53,080 --> 00:33:54,159
Sure, I do.
我当然喜欢。

414
00:33:54,420 --> 00:33:55,460
You do?
你也喜欢？

415
00:33:55,720 --> 00:33:58,680
Well, there's nothing like a relationship with a horse, is there?
没什么比和马谈恋爱更好的了，不是吗？

416
00:33:59,200 --> 00:34:00,680
They're beautiful animals.
它们是美丽的动物。

417
00:34:02,200 --> 00:34:02,960
Mm-hmm.

418
00:34:08,999 --> 00:34:10,999
(加利福尼亚州，马里布)

419
00:34:14,499 --> 00:34:15,979
You look good on the horse.
你在马背上，看着真不错。

420
00:34:16,079 --> 00:34:17,300
Oh, thank you.
哦，谢谢你。

421
00:34:19,199 --> 00:34:20,399
I have a confession to make.
我要坦白一件事。

422
00:34:20,680 --> 00:34:21,719
Oh, what's that?
哦，是什么？

423
00:34:21,819 --> 00:34:23,019
I don't ride horses.
我其实不会骑马。

424
00:34:23,239 --> 00:34:24,279
Really?
真的？

425
00:34:24,800 --> 00:34:26,039
You could have fooled me.
你差点儿就“蒙骗”了我。

426
00:34:27,719 --> 00:34:29,559
Well, it's beautiful up here.
嗯，这里很美。

427
00:34:29,999 --> 00:34:31,259
Yes, it is.
是的，真美。

428
00:34:31,559 --> 00:34:33,840
I grew up a million miles from L.A.
我在离洛杉矶十万八千里的地方长大。

429
00:34:34,099 --> 00:34:37,519
Yes, you know, I did my first location shoot here, in fact.
是的，你知道吗？事实上，我的第一次外景拍摄，就是在这里。

430
00:34:37,759 --> 00:34:38,760
Really?
真的？

431
00:34:38,900 --> 00:34:39,939
Yes.
是的。

432
00:34:40,020 --> 00:34:45,280
I jumped on the back of that horse, looked
around at all this, and said, "Well, I'm in heaven."
我跳上马背，环顾四周，说:“好吧，我现在天堂了。”

433
00:34:45,399 --> 00:34:46,460
Oh.
哦。

434
00:34:46,600 --> 00:34:47,619
Yeah.
是的。

435
00:34:47,700 --> 00:34:48,719
It's heaven.
这是天堂。

436
00:34:49,380 --> 00:34:50,679
You know why?
你知道，为什么吗？

437
00:34:50,960 --> 00:34:53,760
I have a confession to make of my own, Nancy.
我也要坦白一件事，南希。

438
00:34:55,760 --> 00:34:58,399
Uh, I'm what you call damaged goods.
我就是，人们所说的“残次品”。

439
00:34:59,199 --> 00:35:04,320
Now, I'm divorced, I got kids,
I haven't had a decent role in years.
现在我离婚了，有了孩子，有好多年，没演过正经角色了。

440
00:35:05,200 --> 00:35:06,420
I'm just about broke.
我快破产了。

441
00:35:07,480 --> 00:35:09,160
How's that for a cup one?
听了这，感觉如何？

442
00:35:11,199 --> 00:35:13,320
We're all damaged goods, Ronnie.
我们都是残次品，罗尼。

443
00:35:16,600 --> 00:35:18,200
What's next for you?
下一步，你打算怎么样？

444
00:35:18,600 --> 00:35:22,259
I mean, what do you want out of this life?
我是说，你想要什么样的生活?

445
00:35:23,040 --> 00:35:24,120
I don't know.
我还没想。

446
00:35:24,320 --> 00:35:26,559
I used to have big ambitions, dreams.
我曾经有很大的抱负和梦想。

447
00:35:26,999 --> 00:35:33,219
Now I... I don't know,
I just want to do something good in this world.
现在我…我不知道，我只想为这个世界做点好事。

448
00:35:34,640 --> 00:35:36,040
Make a difference.
有所作为。

449
00:35:37,559 --> 00:35:38,599
I think you've done that.
我想，你已经做到了。

450
00:35:40,800 --> 00:35:42,420
I like to make a difference, too.
我也想有所作为。

451
00:35:45,640 --> 00:35:48,519
But I have figured something out, Ronnie.
但我现在，发现了一些事情，罗尼。

452
00:35:49,360 --> 00:35:50,560
What's that?
什么事情？

453
00:35:50,820 --> 00:35:53,059
It's really hard to make a difference in this life.
这辈子真的很难有所作为。

454
00:35:53,199 --> 00:35:56,199
When you have to do it alone.
当你不得不独自面对的时候。

455
00:36:41,199 --> 00:36:43,199
Are you sure you want to go?
你确定要去吗？

456
00:36:43,460 --> 00:36:46,719
Do you know, this is not exactly an Academy of work stuff.
你知道吗，我这可不是什么能拿“学院奖”的工作。
（奥斯卡奖也叫“美国电影艺术科学学院奖”）

457
00:36:46,819 --> 00:36:50,579
Well, you know we don't like to be
apart, and I love to watch my husband work.
你知道，我们不喜欢分开，我也喜欢，看我丈夫工作。

458
00:36:50,679 --> 00:36:52,899
I know, he works work.
我知道，他就是一“打工的”。

459
00:37:14,400 --> 00:37:17,220
Bye, Patty. Mr.Rankin, your agent's on the line.
再见,帕蒂。兰金先生，你的经纪人来电话了。

460
00:37:17,599 --> 00:37:20,159
Look, Lou, if I go out there, my career, it's...
听着，卢，如果我出去，我的事业...

461
00:37:21,199 --> 00:37:22,400
It's dead.
就完了。

462
00:37:26,679 --> 00:37:28,079
Lou, listen to me.
卢，听我说。

463
00:37:29,559 --> 00:37:31,360
I'm not going out there.
我不会出去的。

464
00:37:32,040 --> 00:37:35,320
It is half-blue ribbon time.
现在是“半蓝带啤酒”时间。

465
00:37:36,159 --> 00:37:37,300
What do you have?
你有什么？

466
00:37:37,400 --> 00:37:39,039
I'll have a half-blue ribbon.
我将有一个“半蓝带啤酒”。

467
00:37:39,719 --> 00:37:41,079
I'll take a half-sponzo.
那我就拿半块海绵。

468
00:37:41,620 --> 00:37:42,660
Oh, yeah.
哦，是的。

469
00:37:44,239 --> 00:37:46,159
Looks like it's been time for bonzo, folks.
亲们，把时间交给邦佐。

470
00:37:48,119 --> 00:37:51,719
Thank you, ladies and gentlemen,
and now the half-blue ribbon dancers.
谢谢，女士们先生们，现在有请“半蓝带”舞者。

471
00:38:11,140 --> 00:38:15,960
Ladies, we happen to have an extra smoke for a clown.
姑娘们，谁正好有多余的烟卷，赏给这个小丑抽一口吧。

472
00:38:16,419 --> 00:38:17,480
Thank you.
谢谢。

473
00:39:10,320 --> 00:39:13,760
This season, I'm sending all my friends Chester Fields.
这个季节，我要把切斯特・菲尔兹香烟，送给我所有的朋友。

474
00:39:14,059 --> 00:39:18,759
Meanwhile, his career as movie star continued to fade.
与此同时，他作为电影明星的职业生涯，继续在衰退。

475
00:39:18,960 --> 00:39:20,880
Wow, I could have had a V8.
哇，我应该来杯V8果汁。

476
00:39:22,199 --> 00:39:25,159
Oh, Ronnie, that's a super smooth shave.
罗尼，刮得真“顺溜”啊。

477
00:39:25,359 --> 00:39:27,400
That's because I used Gillette.
那是因为我用的是“吉列牌”剃须刀。

478
00:39:28,840 --> 00:39:31,840
Soothe your skin with campo, phanique, antiseptic powder.
舒缓皮肤，就用“坎波”牌爽身粉

479
00:39:32,220 --> 00:39:35,840
The movies are at home,honey. They're the perfect snack.
在家看电影，亲爱的。它们是完美的零食。

480
00:39:36,559 --> 00:39:40,360
Icy, the coldest drink in town at a sweet low price.
冰凉，本城最凉爽的饮料，价格又低又“甜”。

481
00:39:40,760 --> 00:39:43,639
Come on, Coleman's. Light my fire.
来根柯尔曼香烟，我帮您点上。

482
00:39:46,240 --> 00:39:50,599
He continued to focus on his role
as the president of Screen Actors Guild.
他继续专注于，他作为美国“演员公会”主席的角色。

483
00:39:52,559 --> 00:39:54,360
Well, he did quite well, actually.
事实上，他做得很好。

484
00:39:54,679 --> 00:39:58,280
But the movie opportunities started to evaporate.
但拍电影的机会，开始消失了。

485
00:39:58,540 --> 00:40:01,540
Yes, he was a B movie star. This is well known.
是的，他是B级电影明星。这是众所周知的。

486
00:40:01,779 --> 00:40:05,860
But what does this have to do with losing our motherland?
但这与我们伟大祖国-苏联的消失，有什么关系呢?

487
00:40:06,660 --> 00:40:09,920
Communism is not the motherland.
共产主义，并不是我们的祖国。

488
00:40:10,800 --> 00:40:12,419
They the motherland.
他们才是祖国。

489
00:40:13,759 --> 00:40:18,800
Tergen Yev, Lev Tostoy,Chekhov, that's the motherland.
屠格涅夫、列夫・托尔斯泰、契诃夫，这些才是祖国。

490
00:40:19,059 --> 00:40:20,260
The motherland.
母亲的国度。

491
00:40:21,999 --> 00:40:23,259
Is he a...
就在这里...

492
00:40:24,319 --> 00:40:25,400
I don't know, but...
我不知道，但是...

493
00:40:26,280 --> 00:40:27,700
I can't.
我不能再说了。

494
00:40:37,899 --> 00:40:38,940
Hello?
你好？

495
00:40:40,799 --> 00:40:41,819
Oh, no.
哦，不。

496
00:40:42,619 --> 00:40:43,660
Ronnie?
罗尼？

497
00:40:49,799 --> 00:40:52,339
Thank you, Lord, for my mother.
主啊，为了母亲，我感谢你。

498
00:40:53,399 --> 00:40:55,599
Take care of her.
在天国，照顾她。

499
00:40:56,599 --> 00:40:58,680
I know you will.
我知道，你会的。

500
00:41:01,679 --> 00:41:05,200
Your gut and faith will serve and test. Come on.
你的内心和信念，将会得到伺服和应验。安息吧。

501
00:41:14,039 --> 00:41:18,960
While he mourned the loss of his
mother and continued to struggle with his career,
当他为失去母亲而悲伤，继续为事业奋斗的时候，

502
00:41:19,440 --> 00:41:21,719
the world was passing him by.
这个世界正与他“擦身而过”。

503
00:41:21,999 --> 00:41:25,879
The United States and Soviet Union now face off in a new Cold War.
美国和苏联在一场新的冷战中对峙。
（共产主义占据古巴，卡斯特罗取得政权）

504
00:41:26,059 --> 00:41:27,480
Nuclear retaliation looms.
核报复迫在眉睫。
（古巴流亡者在猪湾惨败）

505
00:41:27,719 --> 00:41:35,760
The purpose of these bases can be none other than to provide
a nuclear strike capability against the Western Hemisphere.
这些基地的目的，无非是提供，针对西半球的核打击能力。
（苏联在古巴部署核武器）

506
00:41:36,400 --> 00:41:40,960
President Kennedy's blockade stops
the advance of nuclear weapons into Cuba.
肯尼迪总统下令的封锁，阻止了核武器进入古巴。
（肯尼迪让赫鲁晓夫撤走古巴核武器）

507
00:41:41,160 --> 00:41:44,660
（红军在建造柏林墙，分隔百万人民）

508
00:41:44,920 --> 00:41:48,519
Movements across Germany have been stopped
as the East Germans built a war overnight,
东德人在一夜之间制造了一场战争，不仅把国家分开，

509
00:41:48,800 --> 00:41:51,880
separating not only the country, but Davis and family.
也把戴维斯和他的家人分开，德国各地的运动都停止了。

510
00:41:51,980 --> 00:41:55,980
(肯尼迪访问西柏林，支持德国人民，
在勃兰登堡前发表“自由，是不可分隔的”讲话)

511
00:41:56,199 --> 00:42:01,159
He became host of TV show for appliance company.
他为电器公司，在电视上做广告代言人。
（里根，从大银幕转到了小屏幕）

512
00:42:01,199 --> 00:42:06,199
He toured across the country,
meeting factory workers and giving speeches.
他在全国各地巡回演出，会见工厂工人并发表演讲。

513
00:42:06,400 --> 00:42:09,499
He was like politician with no party.
他就像一个没有党派的政治家。

514
00:42:10,360 --> 00:42:13,679
So he decided to set his sights on something else.
所以，他决定把目光，投向其他领域。

515
00:42:13,900 --> 00:42:14,999
Us.
我们苏联。

516
00:42:15,400 --> 00:42:21,440
He devoured books about communism,
espionage, our takeover of Eastern Europe,
他如饥如渴地阅读有关共产主义、间谍活动、我们接管东欧的书籍，

517
00:42:21,880 --> 00:42:24,960
and the construction of the Berlin Wall.
还有关于柏林墙的建造的书籍。

518
00:42:27,280 --> 00:42:29,800
You know, our bed's a lot more comfortable.
你要知道，我们的卧床，已经变得很舒服了。

519
00:42:30,559 --> 00:42:34,039
Well, unless you prefer,uh, political chambers to me.
除非，你更喜欢政治密室，而不是我。

520
00:42:34,239 --> 00:42:36,120
Well, you know that's not true.
哦，你知道那不是真的。

521
00:42:36,320 --> 00:42:38,419
Come to bed, honey. It's late.
上床吧，亲爱的，很晚了。

522
00:42:41,639 --> 00:42:47,039
You know, all they have are missiles and oil.
他们想的，只有导弹和石油。

523
00:42:48,320 --> 00:42:52,119
If we get them to spend money they
don't have, they can't support themselves.
如果我们让他们去花他们并没有的钱，他们就无法养活自己。

524
00:42:52,400 --> 00:42:53,819
The Soviets.The Soviets.
-那些苏联人。 -苏联人。

525
00:42:54,100 --> 00:42:56,139
We've been going about this all wrong.
我们以前一直都做错了。

526
00:42:56,360 --> 00:42:59,380
We don't have to match their missile for missile.
我们根本就不该用导弹，去对付他们的导弹。

527
00:42:59,780 --> 00:43:03,620
All we have to do is just keep up the pressure.
我们要做的就是，保持压力。

528
00:43:04,039 --> 00:43:06,539
We have deeper pockets than they do.
因为，我们比他们更有钱。

529
00:43:06,800 --> 00:43:09,159
In the year I thought I married an actor.
那年，我以为我，嫁给了一个演员。

530
00:43:10,519 --> 00:43:14,440
Well, you can always talk to Dick Nixon, President Kennedy,
嗯，你可以随时和迪克・尼克松副总统、肯尼迪总统

531
00:43:14,880 --> 00:43:17,320
or any of your political friends.
或任何你的政治朋友谈谈。

532
00:43:18,399 --> 00:43:23,920
But why is it that my husband seems
to know what's gonna happen before they do?
但为什么我丈夫，似乎比他们，更早知道会发生什么?

533
00:43:25,199 --> 00:43:32,280
Well, I was a lifeguard at a pub with a swimming hole on a river.
那是因为，我曾经当过河边公共游泳区的救生员。

534
00:43:33,100 --> 00:43:35,159
And I studied that river.
我研究了那条河。

535
00:43:35,839 --> 00:43:38,920
And I learned how to read the currents.
我学会了如何解读水流。

536
00:43:40,939 --> 00:43:42,800
Not just the ones on the surface,
不仅仅是河流表面上的，

537
00:43:43,880 --> 00:43:49,639
but also the ones that were deep
underneath the water, flowing way under.
还有深埋在水下的，在水下流动的。

538
00:43:51,199 --> 00:43:56,159
And I got good at it.
而且我很擅长。

539
00:44:03,999 --> 00:44:07,159
I knew people were in trouble before they did.
我知道，人们在发生危险前，都会有麻烦。

540
00:44:13,059 --> 00:44:16,359
（加州，旧金山
1964年）

541
00:44:17,399 --> 00:44:21,419
Moon, thank you for bringing
your brother up here on such short notice.
穆恩，谢谢你这么快，就把你弟弟带过来。

542
00:44:21,680 --> 00:44:23,719
It wasn't easy. He's not a fan of flying.
这并不容易。他不喜欢坐飞机旅行。

543
00:44:23,960 --> 00:44:26,400
Well, we'll remedy that.Thank you for coming, Mr. Reagan.
好吧，我们为此会补偿的。谢谢您的光临，里根先生。

544
00:44:26,679 --> 00:44:28,159
Thanks for having me, Mr. Tuttle.
谢谢你邀请我，塔特尔先生。

545
00:44:28,519 --> 00:44:31,599
Now, we understand that you jumped the aisle and switched parties.
现在，我们知道你“跳过船帮”，换了党派。

546
00:44:31,880 --> 00:44:33,880
Well, my brother and I both.
是的，我哥哥和我都是。

547
00:44:34,199 --> 00:44:38,280
We came of age under FDR.Our dad, Jack, he was a huge fan.
我们是在罗斯福执政时期长大的。我们的爸爸，杰克，他是坚定的民主党。

548
00:44:38,380 --> 00:44:41,280
And we were proud to be New Deal Democrats.
我们那时，为成为倡导新政的民主党人而自豪。

549
00:44:41,580 --> 00:44:43,380
So why did you leave him?
那你为什么背离他？

550
00:44:43,639 --> 00:44:45,840
I didn't. They left me.
我没有。是他们背离了我。

551
00:44:46,139 --> 00:44:48,919
How do you feel about campaigning for Goldwater?
你对为戈德华特竞选，有什么看法?
（共和党保守派，1964年与肯尼迪竞选总统）

552
00:44:49,119 --> 00:44:52,039
He's gonna get shellacked in
November. No way he takes the White House.
他会在11月被击败的。他不可能入主白宫。

553
00:44:52,599 --> 00:44:55,400
Mr. Tuttle's right. He can't beat LBJ.
塔特尔先生说得对。他打不过林登.约翰逊。

554
00:44:56,360 --> 00:45:00,039
I'm curious, Ron. What would you say is the issue of our time?
我很好奇，罗恩。你认为我们这个时代的问题是什么？

555
00:45:01,400 --> 00:45:05,639
No question about it.Communism and the Soviet Union.
毫无疑问。共产主义和苏联。

556
00:45:06,280 --> 00:45:08,800
Domestic issues is what I'm more curious about.
我更感兴趣的是，国内问题。

557
00:45:10,899 --> 00:45:14,440
What's more domestic than survival, Mr. Tuttle?
还有什么比生存更重要的呢，塔特尔先生?

558
00:45:15,020 --> 00:45:17,719
Communism is the natural enemy of freedom.
共产主义是自由的天敌。

559
00:45:18,020 --> 00:45:21,400
It won't stop attacking us from the outside or the inside.
它会不停地从外部或内部攻击我们。

560
00:45:21,620 --> 00:45:26,079
And it's spreading around the world
while we wring our hands trying to negotiate.
当我们握紧双拳，在与之谈判时，共产主义正在全世界蔓延。

561
00:45:29,639 --> 00:45:32,800
What did I tell you guys? He's not just a pretty face.
我怎么跟你们说的？ 他不只是长得漂亮。

562
00:45:33,360 --> 00:45:36,400
Why don't you put your money
where your mouth is, Ron? Get in the game.
你为什么不把钱，花在你说的话上呢，罗恩？踏入政坛吧。

563
00:45:36,619 --> 00:45:39,079
Support Goldwater and then run for office.
支持戈德华特，然后竞选公职。

564
00:45:39,320 --> 00:45:43,119
Well, he'd win State Senate and a
landslide. State Senate. How's that sound?
-他会以压倒性优势赢得州参议员。州参议院。 -听起来如何？

565
00:45:46,200 --> 00:45:49,839
Well, I played his senator once.
好吧，我曾经扮演过一次他的参议员。

566
00:45:50,719 --> 00:45:52,959
But I never played a governor.
但我从未扮演过州长。

567
00:46:00,519 --> 00:46:08,320
17 years after I had begun following him, he
made his debut on American political stage.
在我开始跟踪他17年后，他在美国政治舞台上，首次亮相。

568
00:46:08,559 --> 00:46:13,599
Well, I'd like to suggest to you there is no such
thing as left or right. There's only up or down.
好吧，我想建议你们，没有所谓的向左或向右。只有上升或下降。

569
00:46:14,240 --> 00:46:17,459
I believe that the issue is confronting us across party lines.
我相信，我们面对的这个问题，是跨党派的。

570
00:46:17,859 --> 00:46:26,679
Now, one side of this campaign has been telling us that
the issues of this election are not the same.
现在，这场竞选的对方，一直在告诉我们，这次选举的议题，是不一样的。

571
00:46:26,779 --> 00:46:30,679
The line has been used. We've never had it so good.
这套台词被用过了。我们已经不想再听了。

572
00:46:30,880 --> 00:46:33,320
Somewhere a perversion is taking place.
某些地方，正在发生着变态的压迫行为。

573
00:46:33,799 --> 00:46:38,599
Should Moses have told the children of Israel
to live in slavery under the Pharaohs?
摩西应该让以色列人的子孙，在法老的奴役下生活吗？

574
00:46:38,699 --> 00:46:40,759
Should Christ have refused to cross?
基督应该拒绝十字架吗？

575
00:46:40,899 --> 00:46:44,959
Should the Patriots have thrown down their guns
and refused to fire the shot heard round the world?
爱国者们就应该放下他们的枪，拒绝发射响彻世界的枪声吗？

576
00:46:46,679 --> 00:46:50,119
You and I have the courage to say to our enemies,
你和我，有勇气对我们的敌人说，

577
00:46:51,280 --> 00:46:58,199
"There is a price we will not pay, a
point beyond which they must not advance."
“有一个开价，是我们不会支付的，那就是他们的‘得寸进尺’。”

578
00:46:59,719 --> 00:47:04,480
We'll preserve for our children this,
the last best hope of man on earth.
我们要为我们的孩子保留这个，地球上人类最后的、最美好的希望。

579
00:47:05,039 --> 00:47:10,239
Or we'll sentence them to take the
last step into a thousand years darkness.
否则，我们就宣判他们，向千年黑暗迈出最后一步。

580
00:47:11,339 --> 00:47:18,400
When great forces are on the move in the world,
we learn that we are spirits, not animals.
当世界潮流浩浩荡荡时，我们知道，我们是有灵魂的，而不是动物。

581
00:47:20,039 --> 00:47:24,280
There's something going on in
time and space, beyond time and space,
在时间和空间中，超越时间和空间的事情，正在发生，

582
00:47:24,840 --> 00:47:28,320
which whether we like it or not, spells duty.
不管我们喜欢与否，这都意味着责任。

583
00:47:29,539 --> 00:47:33,559
You and I have a rendezvous with destiny.
你和我都有个，与命运交会的时刻。

584
00:47:34,199 --> 00:47:37,119
[applause]
[掌声]

585
00:47:38,719 --> 00:47:44,360
Mr. Goldwater lost decisively, but the crusader had arrived,
戈德华特先生输得惨不忍睹，但“十字军战士”已经到来了，

586
00:47:45,320 --> 00:47:50,119
and he was putting us on notice that he was not afraid to take us on.
这个“十字军”让我们注意到，他不怕与我们较量。

587
00:47:59,880 --> 00:48:00,919
Hello.
你好。

588
00:48:01,199 --> 00:48:02,640
Hi, it's you.
嗨，是你俩啊。

589
00:48:03,239 --> 00:48:04,479
Well, yes.
嗯，是的。

590
00:48:04,760 --> 00:48:05,980
What are you doing here?
你俩怎么来这儿了？

591
00:48:06,200 --> 00:48:07,279
Did I win something?
我赢了什么吗?

592
00:48:07,379 --> 00:48:08,460
No.
不是。

593
00:48:08,759 --> 00:48:12,679
We're canvassing the neighborhood, and I'm running for governor,
and I would like your vote.
我们在附近拜票，我要竞选州长，希望你投我一票。

594
00:48:13,119 --> 00:48:15,199
Of course. Of course.
当然。当然。

595
00:48:16,119 --> 00:48:19,120
Now I'm embarrassed. I forgot your name.
真不好意思。我忘了你的姓名。

596
00:48:19,360 --> 00:48:21,440
Do his initials help, R.R.?
请记住他的首字母，行吗？R.R.

597
00:48:22,199 --> 00:48:24,159
[gasps]
[惊叹声]

598
00:48:24,199 --> 00:48:27,280
Eddie! Roy Rogers is here!
艾迪！ 罗伊・罗杰斯来了！
（以演牛仔出名的男影星，还出唱片）

599
00:48:29,400 --> 00:48:31,480
And he's running for governor!
而他要竞选州长啦！

600
00:48:35,880 --> 00:48:40,680
（1966年，加州，洛杉矶）

601
00:48:47,199 --> 00:48:54,639
He was on the U.S. stage now, but my
colleague still refused to take him seriously.
他现在登上了美国的政坛，但我的同事仍然拒绝把他当回事。

602
00:48:55,059 --> 00:48:57,100
After all, is it?
不就是个演员，对吗？

603
00:48:57,820 --> 00:49:00,419
What could state governor do to us?
当上州长，有能把我们苏联怎么样？

604
00:49:00,640 --> 00:49:02,679
[applause]
[掌声]

605
00:49:02,879 --> 00:49:06,179
（1969年，加州，萨卡拉门托，州政府所在地）

606
00:49:06,199 --> 00:49:08,480
The police are overburdened. There's just too many of them.
警察负担过重。他们的人太多了。

607
00:49:08,800 --> 00:49:10,220
Where are these kids' parents?
这些孩子的家长，都在哪里?

608
00:49:10,480 --> 00:49:13,719
They're not all students. Most of the agitators,
they don't even know what they're protesting.
他们不都是学生。大多数煽动者，他们甚至不知道他们在抗议什么。

609
00:49:13,980 --> 00:49:17,039
They're just doing it to do it, and they're getting outside help.
他们只是为了做这件事，他们正在寻求外界的帮助。
(艾德.米斯，州长幕僚长)

610
00:49:17,240 --> 00:49:18,719
They've issued a new set of demands.
他们提出了一系列新的要求。
（比尔“法官”.克拉克，执行州务卿）

611
00:49:18,979 --> 00:49:20,339
Of course they have.
他们当然会有的。

612
00:49:20,480 --> 00:49:22,500
They want you to present them to a person.
他们想让你，把“一个人”展现给他们。

613
00:49:22,760 --> 00:49:28,159
The National Guard, they're on standby.
They can be on site within an hour.
国民警卫队，他们随时待命。他们可以在一小时内赶到现场。

614
00:49:28,259 --> 00:49:33,880
That's going federal.There's going federal ramifications for that.
Communities,schools, especially the press.
这要通过联邦。这将涉及联邦分支机构。还要与社区，学校，尤其是媒体沟通。

615
00:49:35,400 --> 00:49:39,280
They want to talk. Let's go talk.
他们想要对话。那咱们就去和他们谈谈。

616
00:49:43,080 --> 00:49:46,080
（1969年五月15日，加州，伯克利）

617
00:49:53,039 --> 00:49:55,519
Governor Reagan! Make love, not war!
里根州长！我们要做爱，不要作战！

618
00:49:55,999 --> 00:49:59,039
But it looks like him.He can't do either right now.
形势对他来说，就像是，他此刻什么都做不了。

619
00:49:59,599 --> 00:50:00,800
Bill's going to meet us inside.
比尔会在里面和我们碰面。

620
00:50:01,679 --> 00:50:02,880
Just lead the way.
头前带路。

621
00:50:04,039 --> 00:50:06,320
Please, go! Please, go!
请走开吧！请走开吧！

622
00:50:06,559 --> 00:50:09,840
We want to hear you speak openly
about this to the state of California.
我们希望听到，你对加州政府公开谈论这件事。

623
00:50:09,940 --> 00:50:11,639
Well, what do you think I'm doing here?
那你以为我在这里干什么?

624
00:50:11,739 --> 00:50:14,800
If you would come out against a
police escalation, they might listen.
如果你站出来，反对警察升级事态，他们可能会听你的。

625
00:50:14,900 --> 00:50:20,320
When did you ever stand up in front
of your students and beg them not to do this?
你什么时候，站在你的学生面前，求他们不要这样做了？

626
00:50:20,420 --> 00:50:23,519
They told you that they were going to destroy the university
学生们告诉你，他们要摧毁这所大学，

627
00:50:24,199 --> 00:50:26,320
and you sought to go ahead with this construction.
而你却巴不得，继续进行这项“施工”。

628
00:50:26,479 --> 00:50:27,920
But they offered to negotiate.
但他们表示，愿意谈判了。

629
00:50:28,120 --> 00:50:29,139
Negotiate what?
谈什么？

630
00:50:29,239 --> 00:50:30,519
All this happened, professor.
这一切都发生了，教授。

631
00:50:30,800 --> 00:50:33,920
The very first time that some of
you who are old enough to know better
你们中的一些年纪足够大的人，应该更清楚，在第一时间

632
00:50:34,199 --> 00:50:39,039
let students think that they had the right
to choose which laws they were going to obey
让学生们思考，他们有权选择，他们要遵守哪个法律，

633
00:50:39,199 --> 00:50:41,960
as long as it was done in the name of social protest.
只要它是以“社会抗议”的名义下进行的。

634
00:50:42,259 --> 00:50:43,320
I've had it.
我受够了。

635
00:50:45,119 --> 00:50:47,000
I call it the National Guard.
我称之为“国民警卫队”。

636
00:50:48,199 --> 00:50:52,119
(crowd cheering)
[人群欢呼声]

637
00:51:06,199 --> 00:51:07,639
Shh!
嘘！

638
00:51:08,199 --> 00:51:11,159
(crowd laughing)
[人群中笑声]

639
00:51:15,639 --> 00:51:19,079
The protesters pushed him hard, but pushed them harder.
抗议者对他施压，但对他们的施压力度更大。

640
00:51:20,960 --> 00:51:24,880
He was controversial governor,
but limited in what he could accomplish,
他是一个有争议的州长，但他能做的事情有限，

641
00:51:24,980 --> 00:51:28,559
at least as far as the things he cared most about, like us.
至少在他最关心的事情上，比如我们苏联。

642
00:51:30,679 --> 00:51:33,159
He enraged many sympathetic to our calls,
他激怒了许多，对我们的号召表示赞同的人，

643
00:51:33,199 --> 00:51:40,039
but he also inspired many fanatics who would go
to great lengths to get the glimpse of their hero.
但他也激发了许多反共狂热分子，他们会竭尽全力,去看一眼他们的英雄。

644
00:51:42,240 --> 00:51:43,820
Come on.
看呐。

645
00:51:44,079 --> 00:51:45,119
Who's this?
这是什么？

646
00:51:45,760 --> 00:51:49,079
Young man, why are you in my yard?
年轻人，你为什么在我的院子里？

647
00:51:50,679 --> 00:51:53,639
Hey, Mrs. Gump, I'm Dana.
嘿，“老镢头”夫人，我是达纳。

648
00:51:53,919 --> 00:51:57,199
I'm head writer for Youth for Reagan, and they're shutting us down.
我是“里根青年后援会”的首席撰稿人，他们要关闭我们的组织。

649
00:51:57,299 --> 00:51:58,320
I just want five minutes for the gun.
我只想和“老镢头”谈5分钟。

650
00:51:58,519 --> 00:51:59,920
Oh, for heaven's sake.
哦，看在上帝的份儿上。

651
00:52:00,020 --> 00:52:01,159
No, I'll be respectful.
不，我会很恭敬的。

652
00:52:01,199 --> 00:52:05,519
Scouts on. I won't swear or
throw anything, and I don't burn buildings.
我还是童子军。我不会说脏话，也不会扔东西，我也不会烧房子。

653
00:52:05,800 --> 00:52:09,559
No, the problem is,
is that the governor is on a very tight schedule,
不，问题是，州长的日程排得很紧，

654
00:52:09,800 --> 00:52:11,320
and he won't give you five minutes.
他连五分钟，都不会给你的。

655
00:52:11,759 --> 00:52:13,039
He'll give you an hour.
他会给你一个小时。

656
00:52:13,199 --> 00:52:14,200
Sweet!
太可爱了！

657
00:52:14,360 --> 00:52:16,400
No, it's not sweet. You need to go home.
不，不可爱。你要回家去。

658
00:52:16,500 --> 00:52:19,320
Please, just call the office, and
I'll make sure you get an appointment, okay?
请你给他办公室打个电话，我会帮你预约的，好吗？

659
00:52:19,459 --> 00:52:20,540
Ready? Is everything all right?
好了吗?  怎么了？

660
00:52:20,599 --> 00:52:21,619
There you go.
你来了。

661
00:52:21,840 --> 00:52:23,920
These young people spent the night in our yard.
这些年轻人要在我们的院子里过夜。

662
00:52:24,360 --> 00:52:25,719
I just want to talk five minutes.
我只想聊五分钟。

663
00:52:28,940 --> 00:52:31,039
Well, you look tired.How about a cup of coffee?
嗯，你看起来很累。来杯咖啡怎么样?

664
00:52:32,120 --> 00:52:33,440
Oh, yeah, it is.
哦耶，果不其然。

665
00:52:35,440 --> 00:52:37,519
Thank you. I'm sorry. I mean, go.
谢谢你！我很抱歉。我是说，我还是走吧。

666
00:52:40,599 --> 00:52:45,599
So the politician says,"Well, what did I do to deserve this?"
于是政治家说:“我到底做了什么，要受到这样的惩罚?”

667
00:52:45,880 --> 00:52:50,679
St. Peter said, "Well, we didn't know what to do with you
because you're the first politician we've had up here."
圣彼得说:“嗯，我们不知道，该拿你怎么办，因为你是我们这里的第一位政治家。”

668
00:52:52,199 --> 00:52:54,159
Nellie had been gone for a decade,
内莉已经走了十年了，

669
00:52:54,199 --> 00:52:59,760
but the crusader managed to find
others who shared her fundamentalist beliefs.
但这位“十字军战士”设法找到了，其他和内莉有同样原教旨主义信仰的人。

670
00:53:00,559 --> 00:53:05,840
And one evening,our surveillance picked up
one of the strangest exchanges I ever heard,
一天晚上，我们的监控录到了,我听过的最奇怪的对话之一，

671
00:53:06,360 --> 00:53:11,199
involving a pop star,a preacher, and a prophecy.
涉及一个流行歌星，一个传教士和一个预言。
（帕特.伯恩   乔治.奥蒂斯牧师）

672
00:53:12,159 --> 00:53:14,679
If you continue to walk uprightly before me,
如果你继续在我面前，笔直地走，

673
00:53:15,120 --> 00:53:18,559
you will dwell at 1600 Pennsylvania Avenue.
你就会住在宾夕法尼亚大道1600号。
(白宫的门牌号码)

674
00:53:21,300 --> 00:53:22,399
Amen.
阿门

675
00:53:26,599 --> 00:53:28,280
(COUGHS)
[干咳声]

676
00:53:28,420 --> 00:53:30,240
Well, there is something.
那么，我还有些事情。

677
00:53:32,199 --> 00:53:34,039
All right, well, we should probably head out.
好了，我们该走了。

678
00:53:34,480 --> 00:53:35,679
Yes, yes. Thank you, Governor.
是的,是的。谢谢你，州长。

679
00:53:35,779 --> 00:53:37,380
Thank you for coming.
感谢光临。

680
00:53:40,679 --> 00:53:42,679
You can't possibly believe this.
你不会相信这个的。

681
00:53:44,840 --> 00:53:47,079
Doesn't matter if I believe it.
我信不信，不重要。

682
00:53:48,360 --> 00:53:49,400
Did he believe it?
他相信吗？

683
00:53:50,379 --> 00:53:51,599
Who knows?
有谁知道呢？

684
00:53:54,199 --> 00:53:56,199
(SIGHS)

685
00:54:18,399 --> 00:54:20,399
（加利福尼亚州，圣伊内斯山，1974年）

686
00:54:28,400 --> 00:54:38,239
(MUSIC PLAYING)
[音乐演奏]

687
00:54:41,639 --> 00:54:43,840
Well, Bill, there she is.
你看，比尔，这就是“她”。

688
00:54:45,239 --> 00:54:47,079
688 acres and all.
共有688英亩。

689
00:54:47,360 --> 00:54:48,780
That sounds about enough.
感觉足够了。

690
00:54:49,059 --> 00:54:50,260
How much are they asking?
他们要多少钱？

691
00:54:50,500 --> 00:54:53,579
Too much for an honest politician.
对于一个诚实的政治家，实在开价太高了。

692
00:54:54,239 --> 00:54:57,320
Well, it's nothing like stomping around in your own piece of dirt,
那么，这一点也不像在自己的泥土里跺脚，

693
00:54:57,520 --> 00:54:59,119
work and sweat.
要付出劳动和汗水。

694
00:54:59,320 --> 00:55:00,520
Think about your next move.
考虑你的下一步目标吧。

695
00:55:00,680 --> 00:55:01,540
(CHUCKLES)
[轻笑声]

696
00:55:01,640 --> 00:55:02,720
Next move.
下一目标。

697
00:55:04,719 --> 00:55:07,800
No, Détente, unfortunately, won't last.
不，不幸的是，缓和局势不会持续太久。

698
00:55:08,799 --> 00:55:10,840
The Soviets, they're here to stay.
苏联人，他们会来这儿住下的。

699
00:55:11,440 --> 00:55:14,320
There's nothing a retired governor can do about the Soviets.
一个退休的州长，对苏联人无能为力。

700
00:55:15,320 --> 00:55:17,400
Well, you got a point. Not much.
嗯，你说的有道理。但并不充分。

701
00:55:19,079 --> 00:55:20,159
But a president.
但一个总统可以。

702
00:55:21,199 --> 00:55:24,840
Now, he can do a thing or two.
现在，只有他，还能做一、两件事。

703
00:55:25,140 --> 00:55:27,039
(CHUCKLES)
[笑声]

704
00:55:27,239 --> 00:55:36,320
(MUSIC PLAYING)
[音乐演奏]

705
00:55:39,199 --> 00:55:46,639
So, multiply that by a million, double that,
and that's only the surface of how deep it really is.
所以，把它乘以一百万，再乘以一倍，这只是它的表面深度。

706
00:55:47,199 --> 00:55:52,440
It being my love for you,I really love you much more than that.
这是我对你的爱，我对你的爱远不止于此。

707
00:55:52,719 --> 00:55:54,599
I-T-W-W-W.

708
00:55:54,699 --> 00:55:56,580
In the whole wide world.
在整个广阔的世界里。

709
00:55:58,899 --> 00:56:01,119
Reminds me of one of your old movies.
让我想起你演的一部老电影。

710
00:56:01,440 --> 00:56:03,920
I should have Paris all in Minshuler.
我应该把巴黎的一切，都带到明舒勒来。

711
00:56:04,480 --> 00:56:06,960
Well, Nancy Pence, I can roll back and get you one.
南希・彭斯，我可以倒回去，再给你演一遍。

712
00:56:07,220 --> 00:56:08,319
(LAUGHS)
[笑声]

713
00:56:08,499 --> 00:56:15,360
(MUSIC PLAYING)
[音乐响起]

714
00:56:17,299 --> 00:56:19,119
Bill thinks I should run for president.
比尔觉得，我可以去竞选总统。

715
00:56:19,519 --> 00:56:21,760
Oh, Bill thinks so, does he?
哦，比尔是这么认为的吗？

716
00:56:22,039 --> 00:56:23,480
What? You think I'm too old?
怎么？你也觉得我老了？

717
00:56:23,719 --> 00:56:26,840
Oh, you look 20 years younger than you are.
哦，你看起来，比实际年龄小20岁。

718
00:56:27,639 --> 00:56:29,280
Your mind is sharp as attack.
你头脑犀利。

719
00:56:29,679 --> 00:56:32,679
Well, you know I can't do this without your support.
你要知道，没有你的支持，我是做不到的。

720
00:56:33,039 --> 00:56:34,159
You'll always have my support.
我永远支持你。

721
00:56:35,199 --> 00:56:39,159
I know I can't just let you chop wood for the rest of your life.
我知道，我不能让你的余生，都在伐木。

722
00:56:39,360 --> 00:56:40,360
Why not?
为什么不呢？

723
00:56:41,279 --> 00:56:42,360
(LAUGHS)
[笑声]

724
00:56:43,760 --> 00:56:47,679
I've actually been thinking about what
that preacher said by the book.
我一直在想，那个牧师一板正经地说过的话。

725
00:56:47,939 --> 00:56:49,299
You thought he was a kook.
你认为他是个怪人。

726
00:56:49,559 --> 00:56:50,580
Still do.
现在还认为。

727
00:56:51,199 --> 00:56:54,059
But maybe he was onto something.
但也许，他说对了什么。

728
00:56:55,580 --> 00:56:57,859
You just made me to save us.
“天生我才，必有用！”。

729
00:56:58,159 --> 00:57:02,179
(MUSIC PLAYING) (SIGHS)
[音乐响起] [叹息声]

730
00:57:02,379 --> 00:57:04,820
Good evening.
大家早上好。
(1976年，密苏里州堪萨斯城)

731
00:57:05,079 --> 00:57:08,159
Tonight's showdown might be the
most thrilling convention we've ever seen.
今晚的对决，可能是我们见过的最激动人心的大会。

732
00:57:08,559 --> 00:57:13,719
It's a true toss-up between the incumbent president
and a serious challenger from within his own party.
这是现任总统，和来自本党内部的有力挑战者之间，真正的决战。

733
00:57:14,440 --> 00:57:15,519
Take pictures. He can talk to...
要拍照。他能和...谈

734
00:57:15,619 --> 00:57:16,620
What?
什么？

735
00:57:16,799 --> 00:57:19,440
Take pictures. If he can talk to Drew,
Pennsylvania might go our way.
拍照。如果他能和德鲁谈谈，宾州可能会对我们有利。

736
00:57:19,599 --> 00:57:21,979
Okay. I heard James Baker had Pennsylvania locked for force.
好吧。我听说詹姆斯・贝克已经锁定了宾夕法尼亚州。

737
00:57:22,179 --> 00:57:23,239
He said they're in play.
他说了，他们还正进行。

738
00:57:23,339 --> 00:57:24,419
We lost Oregon.
我们输掉了俄勒冈州。

739
00:57:24,519 --> 00:57:25,599
You have enough.
你还有足够的。

740
00:57:25,799 --> 00:57:28,279
You know, Indiana,Florida, or Pennsylvania.
你知道，印第安纳州，佛罗里达州，或者宾夕法尼亚州。
