743
00:57:32,719 --> 00:57:35,239
Here you go.Oh, that's gonna look good. I'll get rid of it.
这就对了。哦，看起来不错。把“里根旧帽子”交给我处理掉。

744
00:57:35,339 --> 00:57:37,400
Okay. We may need to rethink that strategy.
好吧。我们可能需要重新考虑这一战略。

745
00:57:37,500 --> 00:57:42,400
Indiana, Florida, Pennsylvania,I'll get Schweinker to connect
with Drew about Pennsylvania.I'll circle back to Ohio.
印第安纳州，佛罗里达州，宾夕法尼亚州，我会让施韦科联系德鲁
关于宾夕法尼亚州的事。我要返回俄亥俄州。

746
00:57:42,639 --> 00:57:47,559
Okay. I will take Florida and Mike, why don't you go talk
with Rich and Marilyn about Indiana, okay?
好吧。我去佛罗里达，迈克，你为什么不去跟里奇和玛丽莲
谈谈印第安纳州的事，去谈谈好吗?

747
00:57:47,800 --> 00:57:49,119
Hey, hey. We gotta win one for the gimber.
嘿,嘿。我们得为“老镢头”赢一场。

748
00:57:49,379 --> 00:57:50,460
Huh? Come on!
呃？加油！

749
00:57:51,259 --> 00:57:52,280
One, two, three!
一，二，三！

750
00:57:52,519 --> 00:57:53,759
Ready? Ready, go!
加油？加油干吧！

751
00:57:54,199 --> 00:58:01,360
For the next president of the United States,
California cast all 167 for Governor Raul Vega!
为了下届美国总统，加州将167张选票，全部投给了前州长，罗纳德.里根！

752
00:58:03,800 --> 00:58:05,159
Thank you, California.
谢谢你，加利福尼亚。

753
00:58:07,199 --> 00:58:13,239
The Commonwealth of Pennsylvania cast 93 votes for Gerald Paul.
宾夕法尼亚州以93票，支持杰拉尔德・福特。

754
00:58:14,679 --> 00:58:17,880
The West Virginia rally presents its vote.
西弗吉尼亚州的集会，展示了他们的选票。

755
00:58:18,199 --> 00:58:23,519
On behalf of our party's candidate for the presidency,
为了选出代表我们党的总统候选人，

756
00:58:27,000 --> 00:58:29,039
20 votes for Gerald R. Moore!
20张选票，投给杰拉德R.福特！

757
00:58:41,079 --> 00:58:45,159
There is no defeat more bitter than a political defeat,
没有比政治上的失败，更痛苦的了，

758
00:58:46,000 --> 00:58:49,559
especially if you think it is your last chance.
尤其是当你认为，这是你最后的机会了。

759
00:58:49,659 --> 00:58:54,480
And right now I predict that the
American people are going to stay that night.
现在，我预测，美国人民将坚持下去，直到那个大选揭晓的晚上。

760
00:58:55,079 --> 00:58:59,159
Jerry, you've done a good job. Keep right on doing it.
杰瑞，你做得很好。继续做下去。

761
00:59:00,719 --> 00:59:06,239
Ford stole it, sir. He was handing out ambassadorships
and rides on Air Force One like candy to babies.
福特偷票了，先生。他把大使和“空军一号”的位子，像糖果一样分给“政治婴儿”。

762
00:59:07,800 --> 00:59:08,440
Backstage politics.
“后台政治”。

763
00:59:11,360 --> 00:59:12,520
Nah.
不。

764
00:59:14,519 --> 00:59:19,559
What I really wanted, Mike, was to be the guy
who finally got to say "yet" to the Soviets.
迈克，我真正想要的，是成为那个，最终能对苏联人说“不”的人。

765
00:59:25,079 --> 00:59:26,400
Guess where's the gun, Will?
威尔，猜猜“老镢头”往哪儿去？

766
00:59:29,559 --> 00:59:35,159
Democrats and Republicans
presented a united front against us for 30 years,
30年来，民主党人和共和党人组成了反对我们的统一战线，

767
00:59:35,199 --> 00:59:39,519
but we sensed an opportunity with the election of Jimmy Carter.
但我们从吉米・卡特的当选中，感觉到有了一个机会。

768
00:59:40,960 --> 00:59:47,519
Then, in 1979, my worst fears began to take shape.
然后，在1979年，我最担心的事情开始出现。

769
00:59:48,199 --> 00:59:51,119
It is a crisis of confidence.
这是一场信任危机。

770
00:59:51,599 --> 00:59:54,840
Yes, Jimmy, it's a crisis of confidence, all right.
是的，吉米，这是信任危机，对吧。

771
00:59:55,899 --> 00:59:58,159
Are you listening to this?
你在听吗?

772
01:00:01,079 --> 01:00:04,199
We are the greatest country in the world
and we have just forgotten it.
我们是世界上最伟大的国家，我们只是忘记了这一点。

773
01:00:05,800 --> 01:00:07,840
Like I didn't see this coming.
好像我没料到，会这样。

774
01:00:09,639 --> 01:00:10,639
It's okay to say it, Ronnie.
说出来没关系，罗尼。

775
01:00:13,519 --> 01:00:15,719
Okay, I'll say it.
好吧，我就说出来。

776
01:00:16,720 --> 01:00:18,720
I want to run again.
我要在此竞选。

777
01:00:29,580 --> 01:00:31,659
What do you think about that?
你觉得怎么样?

778
01:00:32,199 --> 01:00:34,599
If I can do it all again.
如果我能重来一次。

779
01:00:37,719 --> 01:00:42,079
The public scrutiny, the attacks on your character, all the lies.
公众的监督，对你人格的攻击，所有的谎言。

780
01:00:45,480 --> 01:00:48,880
But mainly, I want you to be happy.
但最重要的是，我希望你快乐。

781
01:00:50,280 --> 01:00:54,199
Well, you already made me the happiest man in the world.
你已经让我，成为世界上最幸福的男人了。

782
01:01:01,360 --> 01:01:06,960
I've had to share you my whole
life, but that's what I signed up for.
我一生都不得不和你分享，但这是我的初衷。

783
01:01:08,840 --> 01:01:10,800
And who I fell in love with.
和我爱上的人一起。

784
01:01:13,899 --> 01:01:16,140
It's not over for you, Ronnie.
对你来说，还没结束呢，罗尼。

785
01:01:17,620 --> 01:01:19,919
You know what you have to do.
你知道该怎么做。

786
01:01:20,600 --> 01:01:23,499
And this time, we'll win it.
这一次，我们会赢的。

787
01:01:36,500 --> 01:01:43,540
No, Mr. President, we don't have double digit
inflation because the people are living too well.
不，总统先生，我们没有两位数的通货膨胀，因为人民生活得太好了。

788
01:01:44,039 --> 01:01:48,559
We have double digit inflation because government is living too well.
我们有两位数的通货膨胀，因为政府生活得太好了。
(1980年，俄亥俄州克利夫兰)

789
01:01:49,479 --> 01:01:53,519
Our first priority must always be world peace.
我们的首要任务，必须始终是世界和平。

790
01:01:54,400 --> 01:01:55,959
The use of force is always the last resort.
使用武力，永远是最后的手段。

791
01:01:56,199 --> 01:02:02,239
These are the kind of elements of a national
health insurance important for the American people.
对于美国人民来说，这些都是善意的“国家健康保险”的重要组成部分。

792
01:02:02,479 --> 01:02:06,480
Governor Reagan, again,typically, is against such a proposal.
而里根州长一如既往地，反对这样的提议。

793
01:02:07,999 --> 01:02:09,259
There you go again.
你又来了。

794
01:02:10,679 --> 01:02:13,960
Next Tuesday, you will all go to the polls and make a decision.
下周二，你们都要去投票，做出决定。

795
01:02:14,920 --> 01:02:18,639
And when you make that decision,
I think it would be well to ask yourself,
当你做决定的时候，我认为你们，最好问问你自己，

796
01:02:19,800 --> 01:02:22,159
are you better off than you were four years ago?
你比四年前，过得更好吗？

797
01:02:22,199 --> 01:02:27,159
Is it easier to buy things in the store than it was four years ago?
现在，在商店购物，比四年前更容易吗?

798
01:02:27,759 --> 01:02:31,559
Is there more or less unemployment in the country?
这个国家的失业率，是高还是低呢？

799
01:02:32,100 --> 01:02:35,119
Is America as respected throughout the world?
美国在全世界，还依旧受到尊重吗？

800
01:02:35,840 --> 01:02:37,559
Do you feel as safe?
你觉得安全吗?

801
01:02:38,559 --> 01:02:41,960
Are we as strong as we were four years ago?
我们和四年前，一样强大吗?

802
01:02:43,280 --> 01:02:49,159
If your answers are yes,
then I think it is obvious who you will vote for.
如果你的答案是肯定的，那么我想，很明显，你会投票给谁。

803
01:02:50,199 --> 01:02:57,440
But if you don't agree,then may I suggest another choice?
但如果你不同意，我可以建议你，另做选择吗？

804
01:03:00,000 --> 01:03:04,320
And will to the best of my ability preserve, protect and defend.
我将尽我所能，去坚守，去保护和去捍卫。

805
01:03:05,199 --> 01:03:11,039
The Constitution of the United States.
美利坚合众国的宪法。

806
01:03:11,220 --> 01:03:12,300
So help you God.
上帝保佑你。

807
01:03:12,380 --> 01:03:13,419
So help me God.
上帝保佑我。

808
01:03:13,640 --> 01:03:14,699
Congratulations, sir.
恭喜你，先生。

809
01:03:19,199 --> 01:03:26,039
We will again be the exemplar of freedom and the
beacon of hope for those who do not now have freedom.
我们将再次成为自由的典范，为那些现在还没有自由的人，带来希望的灯塔。

810
01:03:27,199 --> 01:03:36,639
As for the enemies of freedom, they will be reminded
that peace is the highest aspiration of the American people.
至于自由的敌人，我们将提醒他们，和平，是美国人民的最高愿望。

811
01:03:37,440 --> 01:03:47,199
We will negotiate for it, sacrifice for it,
but we will not surrender for it now or ever.
我们会为它谈判，为它牺牲，但我们现在，不会为它投降，永远不会。

812
01:04:24,899 --> 01:04:30,159
James Baker, Whipsar button 76 working for Ford,
now he's chief of staff.
詹姆斯.贝克，“低声下气的小按钮”，76年还为福特工作，现在当幕僚长了。

813
01:04:30,519 --> 01:04:31,880
That's why he's chief of staff.
这就是为什么，他当幕僚长。

814
01:04:32,159 --> 01:04:35,880
Ed, someone who agrees with you 80% of the time is an 80% friend,
艾德，如果有人，八成赞同你，他就是个“八成的朋友”，

815
01:04:36,180 --> 01:04:38,880
not a 20% enemy.
而不是“二成的敌人”。

816
01:04:39,019 --> 01:04:42,439
Mr. Speaker.
议长先生。
（“小滑头”托马斯.奥尼尔，民主党裔众议院议长）

817
01:04:42,719 --> 01:04:44,719
Mr. President, congratulations.
总统先生，祝贺你。

818
01:04:45,719 --> 01:04:46,740
Welcome to the pigs.
欢迎来到贝格斯酒店。

819
01:04:47,199 --> 01:04:49,400
I'm glad you enjoyed
tonight because tomorrow we go to work.
我很高兴你今晚玩得开心，因为明天，我们就要工作了。

820
01:04:49,679 --> 01:04:54,440
Well, I've been well briefed on you, Tiv.
I've been told I'd better get a pretty good head start.
我已经很了解你了，蒂芙。有人告诉我，我最好有一个很好的开始。

821
01:04:55,139 --> 01:04:56,740
That's very Irish, have you?
这很有爱尔兰特色，你说呢?

822
01:04:56,840 --> 01:04:57,919
Yes.
是的。

823
01:04:58,039 --> 01:05:01,039
You plan on going 10 rounds every day.
That's how we do things here.
你计划每天喝10轮。这就是我们做事的方式。

824
01:05:01,139 --> 01:05:04,039
All right. Just remember, every day has a 6 p.m.
好吧。记住，每天下午6点后。

825
01:05:04,679 --> 01:05:05,719
What do you mean by that, sir?
你这话，是什么意思，先生？

826
01:05:05,840 --> 01:05:09,599
Well, after six, we're not political
enemies. We're just two Irishmen having beer.
六点中过后，我们就不是政敌了。我们只是两个喝啤酒的爱尔兰人。

827
01:05:10,699 --> 01:05:11,760
A deal.
说定了。

828
01:05:14,960 --> 01:05:20,440
Ladies and gentlemen, the first lady
and president of the United States of America.
女士们先生们，有请美利坚合众国第一夫人及总统。

829
01:05:28,899 --> 01:05:30,499
Would you do me a favor?
我有荣幸，和你共舞一曲吗？

830
01:05:45,220 --> 01:05:47,319
Everyone's here for you.
这里的每个人，都为你而来。

831
01:05:47,759 --> 01:05:49,780
Excited for a new tomorrow.
为新的明天而兴奋。

832
01:05:50,599 --> 01:05:54,960
Oh, they're just watching me dance with
the prettiest girl in the world.
他们只是在看我，和世界上最漂亮的女孩跳舞。

833
01:05:57,320 --> 01:06:00,400
You know, they thought about this moment a lot.
你知道，他们对这一刻想了很多。

834
01:06:02,639 --> 01:06:08,159
After 76, I just didn't think it would happen.
在76年失败之后，我只是认为，这些都不会发生的。

835
01:06:09,159 --> 01:06:13,159
I knew it. I knew. I always knew.
我就知道。我知道。我一直都知道。

836
01:06:13,860 --> 01:06:15,139
I always knew.
我总是知道。

837
01:06:35,000 --> 01:06:39,199
Ladies and gentlemen, the president of the United States.
女士们先生们，有请美国总统。

838
01:06:44,199 --> 01:06:45,800
Thank you. Thank you.
谢谢你。谢谢你。

839
01:06:46,440 --> 01:06:47,800
Everybody just be seated.
大家都请坐。

840
01:06:49,000 --> 01:06:50,280
Good morning, everyone. Good morning.
早上好，各位。早上好。

841
01:06:51,500 --> 01:06:55,719
Now, the father can't find his
little optimistic son, so he calls out to him,
现在，父亲找不到他乐观的儿子了，于是他对他喊道:

842
01:06:55,819 --> 01:06:59,599
and the little boy pops out of
that huge pile of manure, says, "Yes, Dad."
小男孩从粪堆里跳出来说:“我在呢，爸爸。”

843
01:07:00,119 --> 01:07:02,920
The father says,"What are you doing in there?"
父亲说:“你在里面做什么?”

844
01:07:03,199 --> 01:07:07,639
And the little boy says, "Well, with all this manure,
I know there's got to be a pony in there somewhere."
小男孩说:“嗯，有这么多粪肥，我知道，这里一定有匹小马。”

845
01:07:10,199 --> 01:07:12,199
Anyway, that was my father's favorite joke.
总之，那是我父亲最喜欢的笑话。

846
01:07:13,199 --> 01:07:19,039
And ladies and gentlemen, we have a
pony ourselves, and it's the American people,
女士们先生们，我们自己也有一匹小马，那就是美国人民，

847
01:07:19,519 --> 01:07:21,840
and we're going to do everything for them that we can.
我们将为他们尽我们所能。

848
01:07:22,460 --> 01:07:24,900
We just have to dig them out.
我们必须把他们从粪堆里，拉出来。

849
01:07:28,039 --> 01:07:35,599
He was the president for one half hour before Iran released the
American hostages they had been holding for a year and a half.
在伊朗释放了，被关押一年半的美国人质之前，他才担任了半个小时的总统。

850
01:07:35,699 --> 01:07:37,399
纽约时报：里根作为第40任总统宣誓就职，承诺美国的恢复时期。
几分钟后，在伊朗的52名人质，经过444天的扣押，飞往自由。

851
01:07:37,540 --> 01:07:41,159
It was morning in America, as his supporters will say.
正如他的支持者所说，这是美国的早晨。

852
01:07:41,199 --> 01:07:50,440
But in just a few days, that morning
nearly disappears as quickly as it had come.
但在短短几天内，这个早晨，几乎消失得和它来的一样快。

853
01:07:52,920 --> 01:07:59,440
You and your forebears built our nation, now help us rebuild it.
你们和你们的祖先，建造了我们的国家，现在帮助我们重建它。

854
01:08:00,079 --> 01:08:01,199
Thank you very much.
非常感谢你们。

855
01:08:13,440 --> 01:08:16,520
Now, I like a brighter, more than a yellow.
You know, Ronnie's must.
现在，我喜欢更亮的，而不是黄色。你知道，罗尼非要这样不可。

856
01:08:17,000 --> 01:08:18,200
What?
什么？

857
01:08:19,279 --> 01:08:21,319
It's all right,ma'am. Your husband wasn't hit.
没事的，夫人。你丈夫没有中枪。

858
01:08:21,560 --> 01:08:22,679
Get me there.
带我去那里。

859
01:08:22,920 --> 01:08:24,239
No, I can't do that.
不，我不能那样做。

860
01:08:24,479 --> 01:08:25,880
Get me there now, or I'm walking.
快送我过去，不然我就走着去。

861
01:08:42,600 --> 01:08:44,920
We're in party three.
我们在3号通道。

862
01:08:53,640 --> 01:08:55,659
Right here under his arm.
弹孔就在他胳膊下面。

863
01:08:59,060 --> 01:09:00,680
You told me he wasn't hit.
你跟我说，他没被击中。

864
01:09:00,920 --> 01:09:02,359
Where was he hit?
他伤在哪儿了？

865
01:09:02,459 --> 01:09:04,260
I don't know.They're looking for the bullet.
我不知道。他们在找子弹。

866
01:09:04,439 --> 01:09:05,800
And Jim Brady was shot in the head.
吉姆・布雷迪头部中枪。

867
01:09:06,039 --> 01:09:09,040
Miss Reagan, I'm sorry. No one's permitted
back there. You don't want to see him in this.
雷根夫人，很抱歉。谁也不许进去。总统不会想被看到，他穿成这样。

868
01:09:09,140 --> 01:09:10,599
He has to know I'm here.
他必须知道，我在这里。

869
01:09:11,399 --> 01:09:12,680
Yeah. Oh, yes.
是的。哦,是的。

870
01:09:12,880 --> 01:09:15,520
Excuse me. Excuse me.
对不起。对不起。

871
01:09:15,620 --> 01:09:19,119
Give him another reason to be single.
He's lost up there on his blood all night.
如果再给他找一个让他单独的理由。他整晚都在上面会失血过多的。

872
01:09:19,319 --> 01:09:20,739
Okay. Get a print.
好吧。准备呼吸机。

873
01:09:21,199 --> 01:09:22,880
Where? Where's Nancy?
在哪里?南希在哪里?

874
01:09:24,599 --> 01:09:25,619
Ronnie.
罗尼。

875
01:09:26,899 --> 01:09:29,319
I forgot to duck.
我忘记躲了。

876
01:09:32,320 --> 01:09:33,740
Try not to duck.
尽量不要说话。

877
01:09:35,500 --> 01:09:36,760
You're gonna be okay.
你会没事的。

878
01:09:37,300 --> 01:09:38,360
Mm-hmm.
嗯，嗯。

879
01:09:39,199 --> 01:09:40,720
You're gonna be okay?
你不会有事吧?

880
01:09:42,199 --> 01:09:43,399
Mrs. Reagan.
里根夫人。

881
01:10:01,600 --> 01:10:03,119
Good evening, Mr. President.
晚上好，总统先生。

882
01:10:04,039 --> 01:10:05,079
Please tell me you're Republicans.
请告诉我，你们是共和党人。

883
01:10:05,199 --> 01:10:09,199
Today, Mr.President, we are all Republicans.
今天，总统先生，我们都是共和党人。

884
01:10:42,760 --> 01:10:44,159
I need your hands.
我需要你的手。

885
01:10:47,600 --> 01:10:51,000
I brought you jelly beans.
我给你带了糖衣果冻。

886
01:10:53,399 --> 01:10:56,000
I knew you'd want them when you woke up.
我知道你醒来后，会想要的。

887
01:10:57,800 --> 01:11:00,279
I had to believe you were waking up.
我得相信，你醒了。

888
01:11:02,199 --> 01:11:03,920
I don't do so good without you.
没有你，我活得不好。

889
01:11:12,960 --> 01:11:17,079
I should have been there.I always walk on your left side.
我本应该去的。我总是走在你的左侧。

890
01:11:18,199 --> 01:11:20,479
No. No.
不。不。

891
01:11:21,739 --> 01:11:23,399
The family and you.
咱家要靠你。

892
01:11:48,159 --> 01:11:51,279
No.
不。

893
01:11:54,199 --> 01:11:58,600
Boy, you don't do anything to get that damn tax cut.
小子，你啥都没做，就能得到那该死的减税提案。

894
01:11:58,820 --> 01:12:02,059
I left specific orders through Democrats within 100 yards.
我通过病床100码内的民主党人，下达了具体命令。

895
01:12:02,199 --> 01:12:03,880
You'll have to grin and barret.
你就偷着乐吧。

896
01:12:05,560 --> 01:12:06,820
How you doing, pal?
你感觉怎么样，伙计?

897
01:12:07,279 --> 01:12:10,640
Well, I don't recommend getting shot.
那我就建议你，别被枪打中。

898
01:12:11,119 --> 01:12:12,159
No.
不会的。

899
01:12:12,560 --> 01:12:15,159
You don't have to think there's...
你们不必认为，这件事有什么...
（指辛克利枪击里根）

900
01:12:16,640 --> 01:12:18,399
Think there was a reason for all this.
认为这件事，有什么原因。

901
01:12:20,399 --> 01:12:22,039
There's a big job left to be done.
还有一件重要工作，要做呢。

902
01:12:22,439 --> 01:12:25,960
And whatever time I have left, it...
不管我还有多少时间，我这条命...

903
01:12:27,179 --> 01:12:28,259
...belongs to him.
...是属于上帝的。

904
01:12:29,599 --> 01:12:39,159
Yea, though I walk through the valley of the shadow of death,
I shall see a no evil for thou art with me.
我虽行过死荫的幽谷，也不见灾祸，因为你与我同在。
（摘自《圣经.诗篇》23：4）

905
01:12:39,800 --> 01:12:44,680
Surely goodness and mercy will follow me all the days of my life.
我一生一世必有恩惠慈爱随着我。

906
01:12:45,139 --> 01:12:48,680
And I won't dwell in the house of the Lord forever.
而我会住在耶和华的殿里，直到永远。

907
01:12:48,880 --> 01:12:51,880
（《圣经》原文是will，内嵌字幕却是won't，译文订正一下）

908
01:12:52,119 --> 01:12:56,439
You know,
you may have been an actor if it wasn't for that amount of years.
你知道，要不是经历了那么多年沧桑，你可能会成为一名演员。

909
01:12:57,280 --> 01:12:59,760
Well, there were too many leading men.
那咱们这里，男主角也太多了。

910
01:13:00,819 --> 01:13:03,820
It should have killed him, and it almost did.
这本该杀了他，也差点杀了他。

911
01:13:04,079 --> 01:13:06,199
Most people don't know how close it came.
大多数人不知道，事情来得有多近。

912
01:13:06,639 --> 01:13:08,060
Did we do it?
是咱们干的吗?

913
01:13:08,799 --> 01:13:11,020
No. We didn't do it.
不。咱可没这么干。

914
01:13:11,680 --> 01:13:18,119
Which isn't to say that some version of a
similar plan didn't exist in a drawer somewhere.
这并不是说，某个抽屉里，不存在类似计划的某个版本。

915
01:13:18,640 --> 01:13:20,499
As it certainly does to this day.
如今做法，当然也一样。

916
01:13:25,479 --> 01:13:28,499
You're who? I'm Dana. I start work today.
-你是谁？   -我是达纳。我今天开始工作。

917
01:13:28,799 --> 01:13:32,640
Right. Is this Knopfseger's idea of a joke?
好吧。这是马克.诺普费勒的创意，来白宫搞笑吗？
(英国“恐怖海峡乐队”主唱)

918
01:13:33,479 --> 01:13:35,720
I suggest you leave before the Secret Service get here.
我建议你,在特勤局来之前离开。

919
01:13:35,820 --> 01:13:38,840
The Secret Service let me in.I mean, you're Mike Deaver, right?
特勤局让我进去的。我是说，你是迈克・迪弗，对吧?

920
01:13:39,140 --> 01:13:41,940
(迪弗当时是白宫副幕僚长)

921
01:13:42,319 --> 01:13:45,680
A speechwriter for the President of the United States.
美国总统的演讲稿撰写人

922
01:13:46,199 --> 01:13:48,359
Dana, you're finally here.
达纳，你终于来了。

923
01:13:49,039 --> 01:13:51,159
Just fluent, sir. I don't even have a place to stay yet.
还算顺畅，先生，我还没找到住的地方。

924
01:13:51,199 --> 01:13:54,239
Did not spend an hour in the long, Mr. President.
来了还不到一个小时，总统先生。

925
01:13:54,680 --> 01:13:56,079
So, you know this gentleman?
你认识这位先生吗?

926
01:13:56,439 --> 01:13:58,239
Yes. We go way back.
是的。我们是老相识了。

927
01:13:59,059 --> 01:14:00,319
Soviet grain report.
关于苏联粮食的报告。

928
01:14:00,779 --> 01:14:03,640
Nice nap. I'll trade ya.
读着就犯困，我和你换一本。

929
01:14:05,640 --> 01:14:09,000
Well, Dana, I want you to hurry up and
settle in, because we have a lot of work to do.
达纳，我希望你快点安顿下来，因为我们还有很多工作要做。

930
01:14:18,260 --> 01:14:19,699
We wear suits here.
我们这里，是要穿正装的。

931
01:14:20,899 --> 01:14:22,380
Right on, Mike.
马上就换，迈克。

932
01:14:25,399 --> 01:14:28,459
Would you maybe have an extra I could borrow before payday?
发薪日之前，你能借我一笔钱吗?

933
01:14:30,380 --> 01:14:32,060
Let me know.
你得告诉我。

934
01:14:34,960 --> 01:14:38,600
First quarter numbers are below expectations.
第一季度数据，低于预期。

935
01:14:39,099 --> 01:14:40,740
Unemployment hasn't budged.
失业率没有变化。

936
01:14:40,960 --> 01:14:44,760
I think we should reexamine some of
the revenue enhancers on the table, sir.
先生，我认为，我们应该重新考虑一些增加税收的办法。

937
01:14:45,099 --> 01:14:46,560
Revenue enhancers?
税收强心针吗？

938
01:14:47,320 --> 01:14:50,199
R- Is that what you're calling tax increases?
这就是你所说的增税吗？

939
01:14:51,199 --> 01:14:56,760
These days in Washington, I told the
American people that I would lower taxes.
这些天在华盛顿，我告诉美国人民，我将降低税收。

940
01:14:57,399 --> 01:15:01,600
So if that's what you really think, then what
the hell are you doing in my administration?
如果你真这么想，那你在我的政府里，是干什么的？

941
01:15:02,680 --> 01:15:05,680
Mr. President, we simply have to balance this budget.
总统先生，我们必须平衡预算。

942
01:15:05,780 --> 01:15:08,520
You know, I learned a thing or two about economics.
你知道，我学了一些经济学的知识。

943
01:15:08,880 --> 01:15:11,279
I had majored in economics at Eureka College.
我在尤里卡学院主修经济学。

944
01:15:11,379 --> 01:15:13,980
Now, it wasn't your Ivy League college.
当然，它不如你读的“常春藤盟校”。

945
01:15:14,120 --> 01:15:16,920
But there I learned about Ibn Khaldun.
但在那里我了解了伊本・赫勒敦。
（中世纪阿拉伯著名哲学家、历史学家、政治活动家）

946
01:15:17,139 --> 01:15:18,359
He was a ruler in Egypt.
他曾是埃及的统治者。

947
01:15:18,399 --> 01:15:25,319
And he had a philosophy that really hit home
when I was in the 94% tax bracket in Hollywood.
当我在好莱坞的缴税档位在94%时，他的哲学，真的击中了我的心坎。

948
01:15:25,760 --> 01:15:29,600
And that is, when taxes are low, people have more money.
也就是说，当税收低的时候，人们有更多的钱。

949
01:15:29,800 --> 01:15:32,720
And when people have more money, they buy more things.
当人们有更多的钱时，他们会买更多的东西。

950
01:15:33,159 --> 01:15:40,239
Now, these things have to be made by other people
who have to hire more people to help them do that.
现在，这些东西必须由其他人来做，他们必须雇佣更多的人，来帮助他们。

951
01:15:40,780 --> 01:15:42,239
And ask for taxes.
并要求纳税。

952
01:15:43,419 --> 01:15:44,920
Well, the good Lord only asked for 10%.
好吧，仁慈的上帝只要求百分之十。

953
01:15:45,319 --> 01:15:47,199
Why should Uncle Sam ask for more?
为什么“山姆大叔”却要求更多呢?

954
01:15:49,199 --> 01:15:52,720
Mr. President, the air traffic controllers are threatening a strike.
总统先生，空中交通管制员威胁要罢工。

955
01:15:52,839 --> 01:15:54,099
Well, can they do that?
他们能这样做吗？

956
01:15:54,199 --> 01:15:55,239
No, sir.
不能，先生。

957
01:15:55,399 --> 01:15:56,420
Legally?
合法吗？

958
01:15:56,520 --> 01:15:59,100
Essential public service. They have all signed a no strike contract.
鉴于从事基本的公共服务。他们都签署了“不罢工合同”。

959
01:15:59,239 --> 01:16:01,300
A contract is a contract.
合同，就是合同。

960
01:16:01,859 --> 01:16:03,700
That's the way I learned it.
我只懂这个道理。

961
01:16:03,959 --> 01:16:06,759
They forfeited their jobs.
他们不得不丢掉饭碗。

962
01:16:08,560 --> 01:16:12,079
If he was willing to risk chaos in his own country,
如果他愿意让自己的国家陷入混乱，

963
01:16:12,520 --> 01:16:15,199
we could only imagine what he might do to us.
我们可以想象，他会对我们苏维埃做些什么。

964
01:16:19,760 --> 01:16:22,840
The Soviets are conducting full exercises right out in the open.
苏联人正在大庭广众之下，进行全面演习。

965
01:16:23,520 --> 01:16:27,840
The German border is quiet, but it looks like the movie
is a brand new SS-20s by rail.
德国边境很安静，但从这部影片看，像是一辆全新的铁轨运输SS20导弹发射车。
（卡斯帕.温伯格，国防部长）

966
01:16:28,059 --> 01:16:30,800
That's confirmed.They're 20 miles east of Berlin.
得到了确认，它们部署在，柏林以东20英里处。

967
01:16:31,979 --> 01:16:35,319
Each rail car contains a ballistic missile with a nuclear warhead.
每节车厢都装有一枚带有核弹头的弹道导弹。

968
01:16:35,600 --> 01:16:38,039
John, how many nuclear missiles do they have?
约翰，他们有多少枚核导弹?

969
01:16:38,179 --> 01:16:39,179
35,000.
三万五千枚。

970
01:16:39,439 --> 01:16:41,239
Officially. And us?
如实说，我们有多少？

971
01:16:41,340 --> 01:16:43,380
25 and change, sir.
两万五千左右，总统先生。
（约翰.波因德克斯特，海军上将，时任国家安全事务助理）

972
01:16:43,679 --> 01:16:48,000
So roughly 60,000 nuclear warheads pointed at each other.
所以，大约有六万枚核弹头，互相指向对方。

973
01:16:48,319 --> 01:16:49,600
Each one can take out a city.
每一个都能摧毁一座城市。

974
01:16:50,000 --> 01:16:51,940
That's about the size of it, Mr. President.
规模就这么大，总统先生。

975
01:16:52,239 --> 01:16:56,439
So while we have been, over the past 10 years,
reducing our military,
因此，在过去的10年里，我们一直在削减我们的军队，

976
01:16:57,119 --> 01:17:01,000
they've been building up their arsenal
and thumbing their nose this at us,
他们却一直在建立他们的武器库，对我们嗤之以鼻，

977
01:17:01,199 --> 01:17:03,800
violating every treaty that we have with them.
违反我们与他们签订的每一项条约。

978
01:17:04,039 --> 01:17:06,119
It's not possible, sir.It's exactly what's happening.
这不合常理，先生，但事情就是这样。

979
01:17:06,399 --> 01:17:08,159
And what have we done about it except take a picture of it?
除了拍张照片，我们还做了什么？

980
01:17:08,299 --> 01:17:15,479
Well, after you fire off the first thousand or so,
there's no one around to keep score, is there?
好吧，在你发射了1000枚左右的导弹之后，就没有人来记分了，不是吗?

981
01:17:15,700 --> 01:17:16,719
It's insane.
这是发疯。

982
01:17:17,840 --> 01:17:20,880
One little mistake.Somebody has too much vodka.
一个小差错。有人伏特加酒喝多了。

983
01:17:22,220 --> 01:17:23,820
None of this matters.
那就没救了。

984
01:17:29,199 --> 01:17:34,159
Thousands were gathered in St. Peter's Square at
the Vatican today,cheering the arrival of the Pope.
今天，数千人聚集在梵蒂冈的圣彼得广场，欢呼教皇的到来。

985
01:17:35,199 --> 01:17:42,880
But soon, gunshots turned the celebration into
horror as the Pope collapsed into the arms of his aides.
但很快，枪声把庆祝变成了恐怖，教皇倒在助手的怀里。

986
01:17:43,359 --> 01:17:47,880
He's in surgery. The official story is
that he was grazed,but it's worse than that.
他在做手术。官方的说法是他被擦伤了，但实际情况更糟。

987
01:17:48,440 --> 01:17:49,840
They gave him his last rights.
他们给了他最后的权利。

988
01:17:51,360 --> 01:17:52,800
What do we know?
我们都知道些什么？

989
01:17:53,079 --> 01:17:55,079
John Paul's from Poland under Soviet control.
约翰・保罗二世来自苏联控制下的波兰。

990
01:17:55,319 --> 01:17:57,159
Polish people want self-rule and democracy.
波兰人民想要自治和民主。

991
01:17:57,439 --> 01:17:59,359
The Solidarity Movement is taking over the nation.
“团结工会运动”正在接管这个国家。

992
01:17:59,920 --> 01:18:03,199
The Pope is with them, basically
giving Moscow the middle finger because he can't.
教皇和他们站在一起，基本上是对莫斯科竖起中指，因为他做不到。
（威廉.凯西，中情局局长）

993
01:18:04,199 --> 01:18:08,399
The home land is basically the second coming.
The writing's on the wall.
这在他家乡，如同基督再生。也是不祥之兆。

994
01:18:08,680 --> 01:18:12,399
This comes from Moscow via Bulgaria, Mr. President.
This is KGB all the way.
这是从莫斯科经保加利亚发来的，总统先生。克格勃的一贯手法。

995
01:18:13,000 --> 01:18:17,000
Well, that doesn't make sense, Bill.
They're either going to create a martyr or
这说不通啊，比尔。他们要么创造一个殉道者，要么，

996
01:18:17,100 --> 01:18:20,439
they're going to unleash the Catholic Church against themselves.
要么让天主教会来反对他们。

997
01:18:23,960 --> 01:18:25,160
They're scared.
他们害怕了。

998
01:18:25,780 --> 01:18:27,059
The Pope lived.
教皇活了下来。

999
01:18:27,199 --> 01:18:34,359
And now, the Crusader and the Pope share the
bond of having survived an Assassin's Bullet.
而现在，那个“白宫圣战士”和教皇，有了从刺客枪口下，幸存下来的共同感受。

1000
01:18:34,800 --> 01:18:38,199
And his new ally just happened to have a billion followers.
而他的新“共情者”，恰好有十亿信徒。

1001
01:19:10,119 --> 01:19:18,159
Get out of Poland. Get out of Afghanistan. Throw away
ten years of treaties and eliminate all nuclear missiles.
滚出波兰。从阿富汗撤军。扔掉十年的条约，消除所有核导弹。

1002
01:19:18,880 --> 01:19:22,199
As they say in America, Briazhnev's mind was blown.
就像美国人说的，勃烈日涅夫的头脑被炸飞了。

1003
01:19:28,199 --> 01:19:36,159
He scribbles a personal note on a
yellow paper. The President of the United States.
他在一张黄色的纸上，草草写下了个人笔记。这个美国总统。

1004
01:19:37,839 --> 01:19:41,040
Now we know we shot him.
现在我们知道，真该毙了他。

1005
01:19:41,720 --> 01:19:43,039
Go on state, department.
你接着说，别介意。

1006
01:19:45,199 --> 01:19:46,259
Thank you.
谢谢你。

1007
01:19:46,520 --> 01:19:48,199
Thank you.
谢谢你。

1008
01:19:52,119 --> 01:19:58,240
And now, enter his new Secretary of State, George Shultz,
the Tiger Man.
现在，他的新国务卿乔治・舒尔茨登场了，人称“虎人”。

1009
01:19:58,679 --> 01:19:59,839
The who?
是何人呢？

1010
01:19:59,960 --> 01:20:05,159
He had a tattoo of a tiger on his ass. How do you know that? KGB.
-他屁股上有个老虎纹身。 -你是怎么知道的？ -克格勃。

1011
01:20:11,199 --> 01:20:18,079
We'll just get this little ceremony over with.
This is what I used to quit smoking back in the sixties.
我们赶紧把这个小仪式结束吧。这是我60年代戒烟时用的零食。

1012
01:20:19,199 --> 01:20:23,240
Oh, I knew it. I knew it.
哦，我看出来了。我知道了。

1013
01:20:23,499 --> 01:20:24,499
What?
什么？

1014
01:20:24,680 --> 01:20:30,680
Well, you can tell a lot about a man's character.
By if he chooses just one color or if he grabs a handful.
你可以看出一个人的性格。看他是只选了一种颜色，还是抓了一大把。

1015
01:20:31,199 --> 01:20:34,199
I see. What does it say about my character?
我明白了。关于我的性格，它能说明什么?

1016
01:20:35,199 --> 01:20:41,880
It says that you're focused,you're determined,
and that you're not easily distracted. You're going to do great here.
这说明你很专注，很有决心，而且不容易分心。你在这里会做得很好的。

1017
01:20:42,679 --> 01:20:43,900
Okay then.
说的没错。

1018
01:20:45,199 --> 01:20:53,640
America has hired us to do two things.
Let them be prosperous again and keep them safe.
美利坚雇我们来，就为做两件事。让社会再次繁荣，并保护人民的安全。

1019
01:20:53,859 --> 01:20:56,680
Peace through strength. May I speak freely?
通过力量实现和平。我可以畅所欲言吗?

1020
01:20:57,059 --> 01:20:58,260
I expect it.
我期待着。

1021
01:20:59,199 --> 01:21:03,159
Clarity is power. Now I believe you are clear in these objectives.
清晰易懂，就是力量。现在我相信，你们对这些目标，已经很清楚了。

1022
01:21:03,199 --> 01:21:05,399
Now the rest of the world needs to be.
现在，在世界其他地区，也需要这样。

1023
01:21:05,680 --> 01:21:07,880
As long as those objectives are your objectives.
只要这些目标，是你的目标。

1024
01:21:08,119 --> 01:21:09,760
They are, Mr. Clark,
他们是的，克拉克先生，

1025
01:21:09,960 --> 01:21:15,160
which isn't to say that I won't push back or voice opinions
if I see conflict in those objectives.
但这并不是说，如果我发现这些目标之间存在冲突，我就不会反对或发表意见。

1026
01:21:15,640 --> 01:21:17,299
That's exactly why I chose you.
这就是，我选择你的原因。

1027
01:21:17,560 --> 01:21:25,659
Peace through strength is just a bit opaque. I need you to
articulate a message about the Soviets that I can take to the world.
通过实力实现和平，有点不透明。我需要你，向全世界传达一个，关于苏联的信息。

1028
01:21:26,199 --> 01:21:34,079
Well, that's simple. We win, they lose. And you can quote me.
嗯，这很简单。 那就是“我们赢，他们输。” 你可以引用我的话。

1029
01:21:36,580 --> 01:21:37,799
Well, that's a clear message.
这是一个明确的信息。

1030
01:22:12,959 --> 01:22:16,159
Let the boy that's been threatening you. Every day.
-就让那个男孩，一直威胁你。 -他每天都这样。

1031
01:22:20,699 --> 01:22:24,760
He'll be there tomorrow too.
That's what bullies do until you stand up to them.
他明天也会在那里的。霸凌者都是这样，直到你勇敢面对他们。

1032
01:22:25,600 --> 01:22:29,020
It's time for you to settle this Dutch. Go on.
荷兰仔，该是你解决问题的时候了。上前去。

1033
01:22:42,099 --> 01:22:43,520
Get him.
揍他。

1034
01:23:15,239 --> 01:23:17,060
It's a little soft.
这有点儿“软”。

1035
01:23:17,599 --> 01:23:19,279
We'll get out there, sir.
我们会改的，先生。

1036
01:23:21,460 --> 01:23:23,159
Dana, a word.
达纳，跟你说句话。

1037
01:23:31,840 --> 01:23:35,119
Well, I see you still have one foot in California.
看来，你一只脚，还在加利福尼亚啊。

1038
01:23:38,760 --> 01:23:45,039
I am about to start the biggest war of this century.
Maybe of all time.
我就要发动本世纪最大的战争了。也许永远都是临战状态。

1039
01:23:46,199 --> 01:23:51,159
And I'm not going to fire a single shot.
I'm going to fight it with words.
我一枪都不会开。我要用“言辞”与之抗争。

1040
01:23:52,199 --> 01:24:01,399
And they have to count every single one of them.
So say what you mean. Mean what you say.
他们必须逐字逐句地计算，我说话的份量。所以，说出你想说的，还要说话算数。

1041
01:24:03,600 --> 01:24:06,680
I need the guy who camped out in my yard. You understand?
我要找那个，在我院子里搭帐篷的人。你明白吗？

1042
01:24:09,880 --> 01:24:13,880
1983年，佛罗里达州，奥兰多

1043
01:24:17,439 --> 01:24:23,039
And let us pray for the salvation of
those who live in that totalitarian darkness.
让我们祈祷，去救赎那些生活在极权主义黑暗中的人们。
（41届全国福音教派协会年度大会）

1044
01:24:24,520 --> 01:24:28,920
Let us pray that they will discover the joy of knowing God.
让我们祈祷他们，会发现认识上帝的喜乐。

1045
01:24:29,840 --> 01:24:34,840
And let us be aware that
while their unelected leaders preach the supremacy of the state,
让我们意识到，当他们未经选举的领导人，宣扬国家的至高无上，

1046
01:24:34,940 --> 01:24:43,160
declare its omnipotence over individual man and predict its eventual
domination of all the peoples of the earth,
宣布国家对个人的无所不能，并预言它最终会统治，地球上所有的民族时，

1047
01:24:43,400 --> 01:24:46,960
they are the focus of evil in the modern world.
他们就成了，现代世界邪恶的焦点。

1048
01:24:48,600 --> 01:24:53,640
It was C.S. Lewis,（英国文学家，《纳尼亚传奇》作者）
who in his magnificent screw-taped letters wrote,
这就是C.S.刘易斯，他在他那封华丽的信中写道，

1049
01:24:54,199 --> 01:24:59,960
"The greatest evil is not done
in those sordid dens of crime that Dickens loved topaint,
“最大的罪恶，并不是发生在狄更斯喜欢描绘的，那些肮脏的犯罪场所，

1050
01:25:00,060 --> 01:25:05,159
nor is it done in the concentration camps and labor camps.
也不是发生在集中营和劳改营。

1051
01:25:05,199 --> 01:25:08,640
And then we see its final result.
然后，我们看到它的最终结果。

1052
01:25:08,740 --> 01:25:15,740
But it is conceived and ordered,clear,
carpeted,warmed,and well-lighted offices
但它是在整洁，有序，干净，铺着地毯，有供暖，照明良好的办公室里，

1053
01:25:15,919 --> 01:25:22,439
by quiet men with white collars and cut fingernails
who do not need to raise their voices
由那些安静的白领，和修剪过指甲的人构思出来的，他们说话从不粗声大嗓儿，
（尤里.安德罗波夫，苏共总书记）

1054
01:25:22,539 --> 01:25:26,159
but speak in soothing tones of brotherhood and peace.
甚至还以兄弟般的情谊，和你平声静气地说话。

1055
01:25:27,199 --> 01:25:35,000
Beware the temptation to ignore the facts of
history and the aggressive impulses of an evil empire."
谨防忽视历史事实的诱惑，谨防邪恶帝国的侵略冲动。”

1056
01:25:39,399 --> 01:25:41,999
（突发新闻）

1057
01:25:42,199 --> 01:25:48,359
I think the president's words were a little irresponsible.
The last thing we need to do is heat this cold war up.
我认为，总统的话，有点不负责任。我们最不需要做的就是，激化这场冷战。

1058
01:25:50,419 --> 01:25:54,920
What is wrong with these people?
I mean, whose side are they on anyway?
这些人怎么了？ 我是说，他们到底站在哪一边？

1059
01:25:55,800 --> 01:25:58,720
You can't pay any attention to that.
哦，亲爱的，你不能把注意力，放在这上面。

1060
01:25:59,320 --> 01:26:02,720
But I have to. Most of the country is paying attention to them.
但我必须这么做。全国大多数人，都在关注他们。

1061
01:26:03,079 --> 01:26:06,359
Well, if you think that got
their own decent and wide, you just wait.
好吧，如果你认为，他们这样，就使自己变得体面和广泛，你就等着吧。

1062
01:26:07,760 --> 01:26:11,039
We have prevented nuclear war for more than three decades.
30多年来，我们一直在防止核战争。

1063
01:26:11,139 --> 01:26:13,359
Recently, however, it has become clear
然而，最近情况变得越来越明显，

1064
01:26:13,459 --> 01:26:18,159
we cannot rely solely on offensive retaliation to maintain peace.
我们不能仅仅依靠进攻性报复，来维持和平。

1065
01:26:18,199 --> 01:26:23,399
I call upon the scientific community,
those who gave us nuclear weapons,
我呼吁科学界，呼吁那些给了我们核武器的人，

1066
01:26:23,499 --> 01:26:28,880
to turn their great talents now
to the cause of mankind and world peace.
现在，是该把他们的伟大才能，用于人类和世界和平的事业上了。

1067
01:26:29,359 --> 01:26:36,180
To build this defensive missile shield,
rendering these weapons impotent and obsolete.
建立导弹防御系统，使这些武器，变得无用和过时。

1068
01:26:36,280 --> 01:26:37,779
If we take these measures...
如果我们采取了这些手段...

1069
01:26:37,979 --> 01:26:42,119
He got the idea from a movie he starred in in 1940.
他从1940年他主演的一部电影中，得到了这个想法。

1070
01:26:42,219 --> 01:26:46,199
And with his economy booming,he now had the money to spend.
随着经济的繁荣，他现在有钱花了。

1071
01:26:46,899 --> 01:26:50,520
But it didn't exist. Small detail.
-但这是不存在的。  -耍的小伎俩。

1072
01:26:51,299 --> 01:26:52,720
Small detail?
小伎俩？

1073
01:26:53,119 --> 01:26:56,720
Let's just say he was characteristically optimistic.
这么说吧，他是个典型的乐观主义者。

1074
01:26:56,979 --> 01:26:58,180
So he was lying.
所以，他在撒谎。

1075
01:26:58,600 --> 01:26:59,800
Eat something.
吃点儿东西吧。

1076
01:27:00,159 --> 01:27:03,840
It didn't exist. It was science fiction. But the missiles...
它不存在。这是科幻小说。但是导弹...

1077
01:27:04,079 --> 01:27:05,279
The missiles did.
导弹可是真的。

1078
01:27:06,439 --> 01:27:11,880
Doesn't matter. The Crusader was making his move. And we knew it.
没关系。那个“白宫圣战士”开始行动了。我们知道了这一点。

1079
01:27:14,920 --> 01:27:16,399
And then something happened.
然后，就发生了一些事情。

1080
01:27:18,899 --> 01:27:20,180
Like what?
发生什么了？

1081
01:27:23,680 --> 01:27:27,880
（1983年九月1日，苏联萨哈林岛附近）

1082
01:27:37,399 --> 01:27:41,920
Canadian Airlines, you are in Soviet airspace. Move out, now.
大韩航空航机，你们已进入苏联领空。请立刻离开。

1083
01:27:55,420 --> 01:27:58,420
指挥台，他们没有应答，我估计，这是商业飞行。

1084
01:27:58,620 --> 01:27:59,620
把它打下来！

1085
01:27:59,720 --> 01:28:00,920
你确定吗？

1086
01:28:01,120 --> 01:28:03,620
-那架飞机在闪灯!
-把它打下来!

1087
