蓝莓的。

1171
01:35:02,000 --> 01:35:03,060
Blueberries.
蓝莓的。

1172
01:35:03,119 --> 01:35:04,200
Yes, yes.
是的，是的。

1173
01:35:05,680 --> 01:35:08,399
It's a little early in the morning.
现在还早着呢。

1174
01:35:10,199 --> 01:35:11,319
And you're small, Barry.
你太小了，巴里。

1175
01:35:12,359 --> 01:35:14,920
Mr. Truitt, your question to President Reagan.
特鲁伊特先生，你要问里根总统的问题。

1176
01:35:15,319 --> 01:35:17,560
Mr. President, I want to raise an issue that I think
总统先生，我想提出一个问题，我认为

1177
01:35:17,660 --> 01:35:22,720
has been lurking out there for two or three weeks
and cast it specifically in national security terms.
这个问题已经在那里潜伏了两三个星期，并将其具体地投放在，国家安全方面。

1178
01:35:23,039 --> 01:35:25,359
You already are the oldest president in history,
您已经是历史上年龄最大的总统，

1179
01:35:25,459 --> 01:35:29,720
and some of your staff say that you were tired
after your most recent encounter with Mr. Mondale.
您的一些工作人员说，在最近一次与蒙代尔先生会面后，您感到很疲惫。

1180
01:35:30,279 --> 01:35:31,720
I recall yet that President Kennedy
我记得，肯尼迪总统

1181
01:35:31,920 --> 01:35:35,319
had to go for days on end with very little sleep
during the Cuba Missile Crisis.
在古巴导弹危机期间，他不得不连续几天工作，几乎没有睡觉。

1182
01:35:35,960 --> 01:35:39,399
Is there any doubt in your mind
that you would be able to function in such circumstances?
你有没有怀疑过，在这种情况下，你还能正常工作?

1183
01:35:40,479 --> 01:35:41,720
Not at all, Mr. Truitt.
一点也不，特鲁伊特先生。

1184
01:35:42,520 --> 01:35:47,840
And I want you to know
that also I will not make age and issue in this campaign.
我也想让你们知道，我不会在这次竞选中，把年龄和议题扯上关系。

1185
01:35:47,940 --> 01:35:54,640
I will not, for political purposes,
exploit my opponents' youth and inexperience.
我不会出于政治目的，利用对手的年轻和缺乏经验。

1186
01:35:54,939 --> 01:35:55,939
[LAUGHTER]
[笑声]

1187
01:35:56,339 --> 01:35:57,720
[CHEERING]
[欢呼声]

1188
01:35:58,639 --> 01:36:01,460
And with that one thrust of wit,
凭借这一机智，

1189
01:36:06,660 --> 01:36:08,860
he turned the tide.
他扭转了局面。

1190
01:36:11,319 --> 01:36:14,300
[MUSIC PLAYING]
[音乐响起]

1191
01:36:14,500 --> 01:36:16,200
里根525票，蒙代尔13票

1192
01:36:20,840 --> 01:36:24,840
USA! USA! USA!
美国！美国！美国！

1193
01:36:26,279 --> 01:36:31,439
USA!
美国！
（约翰.巴雷特，特勤局侍卫）

1194
01:36:31,639 --> 01:36:34,339
-你要见我吗？长官。   -就这样吧，把这事查清楚。

1195
01:36:36,239 --> 01:36:39,839
嗨，约翰，听说你是个好骑手。

1196
01:36:40,039 --> 01:36:43,039
是的，我们宾州罗芬堡人，一辈子都在马背上度过。

1197
01:36:43,239 --> 01:36:44,239
为什么问我这个？

1198
01:36:44,439 --> 01:36:47,139
我们有个任务，派你在南加州的原野上骑马。

1199
01:36:47,339 --> 01:36:49,139
什么类型的任务？

1200
01:36:49,339 --> 01:36:55,539
咱们这里没人能骑马，对于怎么能让马跑起来，你应该是个行家。

1201
01:36:55,739 --> 01:36:57,839
你是说骑马策奔吧。

1202
01:36:58,039 --> 01:36:59,439
怎么说都行。

1203
01:36:59,640 --> 01:37:02,760
But do you want to head up that detail when we travel?
但你想在我们旅行时，着手处理这些细节吗？

1204
01:37:05,960 --> 01:37:10,439
So I'd be riding horses with the president.
这样，我就能和总统一起骑马了。

1205
01:37:11,000 --> 01:37:12,239
Giddy up.
起马快跑

1206
01:37:15,039 --> 01:37:16,059
OK.
好吧。

1207
01:37:17,680 --> 01:37:20,199
[MUSIC PLAYING]
[俄罗斯音乐响起]

1208
01:37:22,079 --> 01:37:27,439
Unlike other presidents, the Crusader was in no rush to meet with us.
与其他总统不同，“圣战士”并不急于与我们会面。

1209
01:37:28,560 --> 01:37:30,119
This created a problem.
这就产生了一个问题。

1210
01:37:32,640 --> 01:37:35,079
1982年，列奥尼德.勃烈日涅夫葬礼。

1211
01:37:35,960 --> 01:37:37,039
Here's the latest.
这是最新的。

1212
01:37:41,800 --> 01:37:44,359
1984年，尤里.安德罗波夫葬礼

1213
01:37:46,439 --> 01:37:50,039
It's-- it's so good.
这个...这个很不错。

1214
01:37:58,560 --> 01:38:01,079
1985年，康斯坦丁.契尔年科葬礼

1215
01:38:03,600 --> 01:38:06,639
How can I talk to them if they keep dying on me?
如果他们一直死在我面前，我怎么跟他们谈话？

1216
01:38:11,019 --> 01:38:15,559
We are starving for energy, Ron.And we've got to get it somewhere.
我们急需能源，罗恩。我们得找个地方，把它弄出来。
（英国首相，玛格丽特.撒契尔）

1217
01:38:15,659 --> 01:38:17,920
And we can't afford what we've been paying.
我们付不起，我们一直在付的钱了。

1218
01:38:18,079 --> 01:38:24,960
But buying it from the Soviet Union,you know that that
money is going directly into a missile pointed at you.
但从苏联买石油天然气，你要知道，那笔钱会直接用在，瞄准英伦三岛的导弹上。

1219
01:38:25,520 --> 01:38:29,279
Mr. President, give them an alternative.
总统先生，给女王臣民一个选择吧。

1220
01:38:30,359 --> 01:38:37,520
The Saudis have agreed to increase oil production,
as long as we buy it from them, not the Russians.
沙特同意增加石油产量，只要我们从他们那里购买，而不是从俄罗斯购买。

1221
01:38:38,359 --> 01:38:41,600
And if we can get our friends to go along with us--
如果，我们能让我们的朋友们，赞同我们...

1222
01:38:41,800 --> 01:38:44,920
And you can sell this at home to your Texans.
你可以在国内，让你们的德州佬们接受这个建议。

1223
01:38:45,199 --> 01:38:47,960
It'll drop oil to under $10 a barrel.
油价将跌至每桶10美元以下。

1224
01:38:48,060 --> 01:38:50,439
Oh, I'll take a political hit for it.That's for sure.
哦，我将为此遭受政治打击。肯定会的。

1225
01:38:50,600 --> 01:38:52,119
And Texans love to make money.
何况，德州佬还那么地喜欢赚钱。

1226
01:38:52,319 --> 01:38:53,760
Yes, they do.We all do.
是的，他们会的。我们都会的。

1227
01:38:54,199 --> 01:38:56,479
But they love their freedom even more.
但他们更爱他们的自由。

1228
01:38:56,959 --> 01:39:01,020
First, the evil empire, now this.
先是邪恶帝国，现在又是这个。

1229
01:39:01,679 --> 01:39:04,379
You're certainly not looking to make friends.
你显然不是想交朋友。

1230
01:39:04,600 --> 01:39:05,800
No, I'm not.
不，我不是。

1231
01:39:05,900 --> 01:39:07,340
But perhaps you should.
但也许你应该这么做。

1232
01:39:07,440 --> 01:39:09,439
I met then your man, Gorbachev.
我见过你想见的人，戈尔巴乔夫。

1233
01:39:09,479 --> 01:39:12,039
He has a very different kind of Russian.
他和其他俄国人不同。

1234
01:39:12,319 --> 01:39:18,680
And I told him you were a very, very different kind of an American.
我告诉他，你是一个非常与众不同的美国人。

1235
01:39:24,159 --> 01:39:24,439
All right.
好吧。

1236
01:39:28,939 --> 01:39:33,159
Good evening.President Reagan is in Geneva tonight,
ready for the Gorbachev summit.
晚上好。里根总统今晚在日内瓦，准备参加与戈尔巴乔夫的高峰会晤。

1237
01:39:33,359 --> 01:39:35,659
1985年，瑞士日内瓦

1238
01:39:35,880 --> 01:39:39,560
The Baron is honored to have you stay at his home on this occasion.
男爵很荣幸，们你能在这个时候，住在他家里。

1239
01:39:39,760 --> 01:39:40,819
Thank you.
谢谢你。

1240
01:39:40,960 --> 01:39:43,560
Please let him know how much we appreciate it.
请让他知道，我们有多感激。

1241
01:39:44,420 --> 01:39:46,159
The goldfish.
金鱼。

1242
01:39:47,119 --> 01:39:51,000
It seems that the Baron's son is very attached to us.
看来男爵的儿子很喜欢我们。
（欢迎你，总统先生）

1243
01:39:51,239 --> 01:39:53,479
It needs to be fed twice every day.
每天需要喂食两次。

1244
01:39:53,640 --> 01:39:55,720
Well, I will do it personally.
那我会亲自来喂食的。

1245
01:39:59,439 --> 01:40:01,800
There are a few things I can do myself, you know.
有几件事我自己能做。

1246
01:40:09,239 --> 01:40:10,400
I've arrived.
我来了。

1247
01:40:11,380 --> 01:40:12,479
Oh, then.
哦，好的。

1248
01:40:12,760 --> 01:40:13,819
Yes.
是的。

1249
01:40:14,619 --> 01:40:16,060
Here we go.
我们这就走。

1250
01:40:16,320 --> 01:40:17,500
Oh, no.
哦，不。

1251
01:40:17,700 --> 01:40:18,779
Kotov.
脱下来。

1252
01:40:19,199 --> 01:40:20,399
Below freezing out there.
外面的气温低于冰点。

1253
01:40:20,600 --> 01:40:22,760
The whole world is  watching this meeting, George.
全世界都在关注这次会议，乔治。

1254
01:40:22,880 --> 01:40:25,720
He needs to look his best, and that overcoat is not working.
他需要打扮得漂漂亮亮的，那件大衣不合适。

1255
01:40:25,960 --> 01:40:30,600
Well, you guys are in charge of policy,
but even the leader of the free world has a boss.
但即使是自由世界的领袖，也是有老板的，你们负责政策。

1256
01:40:31,400 --> 01:40:33,200
She's in charge of presentation.
她负责仪表。

1257
01:40:36,840 --> 01:40:45,279
Before the summit had begun, we found ourselves already at a
disadvantage as the president looked better than the general secretary.
在峰会开始之前，我们发现自己已经处于不利地位，因为总统看起来，比总书记好。

1258
01:40:50,640 --> 01:40:53,840
[戈尔巴乔夫的俄语]

1259
01:40:54,040 --> 01:40:56,040
...让我把答复，重申一下。

1260
01:41:02,239 --> 01:41:09,399
The Crusader took an all-instrad,hearing it for what it was.
“十字军战士”对于他听到一切，都毫不畏惧。

1261
01:41:11,539 --> 01:41:17,039
Mandatory messaging from the party.
...来自他们党内的强迫性的讯息。

1262
01:41:20,060 --> 01:41:26,399
As I see it, we don't mistrust each other because we're armed.
正如我所看到的,因为我们发展军备，导致我们互不信任,。

1263
01:41:27,520 --> 01:41:30,600
We're armed because we mistrust each other.
因为我们互不信任，我们才发展军备。

1264
01:41:32,640 --> 01:41:35,880
But I think that we both agree on the most important thing.
但我认为，我们都同意最重要的事情。

1265
01:41:36,840 --> 01:41:42,899
A nuclear war can never be won and must never be fought.
一场核战争，永远不会获胜，所以绝不能被发动。

1266
01:41:45,940 --> 01:41:47,880
He's definitely ambiguous.
他绝对是模棱两可的。

1267
01:41:48,359 --> 01:41:50,880
It's perfectly clear there's nothing ambiguous about it.
很明显，在这一点上，丝毫不能含糊。

1268
01:41:51,119 --> 01:41:52,920
You can't come out ahead as you usually do.
你们不能像往常那样，取得优势。

1269
01:41:53,119 --> 01:41:54,800
Violations after violation.
一再违反条约。

1270
01:41:55,039 --> 01:41:56,640
So one and two.
一项，还有两项。

1271
01:41:56,740 --> 01:41:57,799
Violations.
违反。

1272
01:41:57,820 --> 01:42:00,080
This is nothing more than your militarizing space.
这只不过是因为，你们在搞太空军事化。

1273
01:42:05,560 --> 01:42:08,039
I saw a gentle smile.
我看到一个绅士般的笑容。

1274
01:42:08,320 --> 01:42:10,560
It never left his face.
这笑容，常挂在他脸上。

1275
01:42:10,879 --> 01:42:13,119
He was disarming.
他那时是毫无戒备的。

1276
01:42:13,560 --> 01:42:17,520
But still, he was the zealot that called us an evil empire.
但他依旧还是那个，称我们为“邪恶帝国”的反共狂热分子。

1277
01:42:17,919 --> 01:42:20,160
We could not let our guard down.
我们不能放松警惕。

1278
01:42:20,439 --> 01:42:26,199
You know, I used to do a little acting
a couple of hundred years ago back in Hollywood.
你们知道，好多年前，我在好莱坞做过一点表演。

1279
01:42:26,680 --> 01:42:29,279
Let me show you how we used to handle this sort of thing.
让我告诉你们，我们过去是怎么处理这种事情的。

1280
01:42:37,939 --> 01:42:39,160
Take two.
接受两项吧。

1281
01:42:41,960 --> 01:42:42,560
Hello, McHale.
你好，米哈伊。

1282
01:42:42,840 --> 01:42:44,100
My name's Iran.
请叫我，罗恩。

1283
01:42:48,400 --> 01:42:50,439
How would you like to go for a little walk?
你想去散个步吗?

1284
01:43:02,399 --> 01:43:06,159
What they say about you is the president.
他们关于你，所说的就是，你是个总统。

1285
01:43:06,420 --> 01:43:09,199
He picks your pocket and makes you feel good about it.
他会在扒窃你的口袋时，让你感觉良好。

1286
01:43:10,039 --> 01:43:12,800
Well, I've had much worse said about me before.
我以前，被人说得更恶劣。

1287
01:43:13,039 --> 01:43:14,260
Way worse.
更恶劣的方式。

1288
01:43:14,940 --> 01:43:23,680
I want to let you know that we seek the same thing, McHale.
我想让你知道，我们的目标是一致的，米哈伊。

1289
01:43:24,560 --> 01:43:26,020
Do we, Ron?
我们一致吗？罗恩。

1290
01:43:26,780 --> 01:43:29,040
We are not here because we need to be.
我们来这里，不是因为我们需要来。

1291
01:43:29,680 --> 01:43:31,840
We desire peace just as you do.
我们和你们一样渴望和平。

1292
01:43:32,880 --> 01:43:35,640
But your proposal is not so simple.
但你的提议，没那么简单。

1293
01:43:36,359 --> 01:43:39,319
Oh, actually, it is very simple.
哦，实际上，它很简单。

1294
01:43:40,620 --> 01:43:41,880
It's just not easy.
这并不容易。

1295
01:43:43,720 --> 01:43:48,279
But I believe that you and I, we can do it.
但我相信，你和我，我们可以做到。

1296
01:43:48,760 --> 01:43:50,240
In fact, we must.
事实上，我们必须这样做。

1297
01:43:50,939 --> 01:43:52,199
The world demands it.
世界需要它。

1298
01:43:52,600 --> 01:43:54,800
And after all,isn't that who we work for?
毕竟，难道我们不就是为了全世界人民工作吗？

1299
01:43:55,039 --> 01:43:57,240
The people and the man upstairs.
人民，和天堂上的那个人。

1300
01:43:57,479 --> 01:43:59,640
The man upstairs.
天堂上的那个人。

1301
01:44:01,279 --> 01:44:03,960
My grandmother was a Christian woman.
我的祖母是一位基督徒。

1302
01:44:04,079 --> 01:44:06,139
Go to church every day.
每天去教堂。

1303
01:44:06,359 --> 01:44:10,119
And afterwards say,"Micha铆l, I went to church today.
每次回来后，她都说，“米哈伊，我今天去了教堂。

1304
01:44:10,560 --> 01:44:14,119
I prayed for the atheist.I prayed for you."
我为无神论者祈祷。我为你祈祷。”

1305
01:44:14,960 --> 01:44:19,960
Well, I think that your grandmother and my mother
could have been very good friends.
我觉得，你奶奶和我妈妈，本可以成为好朋友的。

1306
01:44:21,759 --> 01:44:23,399
So you're the Tiger Man.
所以，你就是那个“虎人”。

1307
01:44:23,660 --> 01:44:24,739
Excuse me?
什么？

1308
01:44:24,999 --> 01:44:26,020
Tiger Man?
虎人？

1309
01:44:26,159 --> 01:44:28,359
Like American baseball, very much.
你非常喜欢美国棒球。

1310
01:44:28,620 --> 01:44:29,920
Well, yeah, who's your favorite team?

1311
01:44:30,239 --> 01:44:31,379
New York Yankees.
纽约扬基队。

1312
01:44:31,580 --> 01:44:32,639
And you?
你呢？

1313
01:44:32,999 --> 01:44:34,160
St. Louis Cardinals.
圣路易斯红雀队。

1314
01:44:35,600 --> 01:44:37,159
Game seven, World Series.
世界棒球大赛中，连胜七场。

1315
01:44:37,859 --> 01:44:40,739
Very sorry.But what series?
很遗憾。这是个什么样的大赛事？

1316
01:44:40,939 --> 01:44:41,940
Hold it.
等一下。

1317
01:44:42,119 --> 01:44:44,159
Next time you're in the States, I'll make sure you get to a game.
下次你来美国的时候，我一定让你去看一场比赛。

1318
01:44:46,099 --> 01:44:47,319
No, no, no, no, no.
不，不，不。

1319
01:44:47,419 --> 01:44:48,519
Let them talk.
让他们谈吧。

1320
01:44:48,680 --> 01:44:49,920
You go in there, you're fired.
你要是进屋去，你就被解雇了。

1321
01:44:53,179 --> 01:44:54,600
Tiger Man.
他才是“虎人”。

1322
01:44:56,520 --> 01:45:09,720
My proposal is this,that you and I, by the time that I leave office,
can reduce our missile counts by half.
我的建议是，在我卸任之前，你和我，可以将我们的导弹数量减少一半。

1323
01:45:14,239 --> 01:45:16,159
I'm not a patient man either.
我同样，不是个有耐心的人。

1324
01:45:17,640 --> 01:45:23,159
I do not intend to leave office before they are gone, completely.
在导弹们完全消失之前，我不打算离任。

1325
01:45:39,339 --> 01:45:40,399
Oh, no.
噢，不要。

1326
01:45:40,979 --> 01:45:42,439
Honey, look what I've done.
亲爱的，看看我都干了啥？

1327
01:45:42,680 --> 01:45:43,699
Oh, dear.
哦，亲爱的。

1328
01:45:44,119 --> 01:45:45,760
Maybe we can find another one.
也许，我们可以再去找一条。

1329
01:45:46,399 --> 01:45:48,560
Mr. President, we go live in five minutes.
总统先生，五分钟后开始直播。

1330
01:45:48,959 --> 01:45:50,820
I think we should find another one.
我觉得，我们应该再找一条。

1331
01:45:50,960 --> 01:45:52,039
No.
不。

1332
01:45:52,199 --> 01:45:53,880
Every kid knows his goldfish.
每个孩子都认识他的金鱼。

1333
01:45:54,359 --> 01:45:55,600
I'm going to write him a note.
我要给他写张纸条。

1334
01:45:55,860 --> 01:45:57,159
We need to go now.
我们现在就要走了。

1335
01:45:57,439 --> 01:45:59,119
I mean, the entire world is waiting.
全世界都在等着你呢。

1336
01:45:59,400 --> 01:46:00,880
The world can wait.
全世界可以等。

1337
01:46:01,800 --> 01:46:03,479
I'm going to write him a note.
我要给他写道歉信。

1338
01:46:05,500 --> 01:46:06,720
It's my Ronnie.
这就是我的罗尼。

1339
01:46:08,320 --> 01:46:09,579
I have to wait.
我也得等。

1340
01:46:10,199 --> 01:46:13,880
Nothing was really agreed to yet beyond agreeing to meet again.
除了同意再次会面之外，没有达成任何真正的协议。

1341
01:46:14,279 --> 01:46:17,680
But the Soviet Union and USA were talking to one another,
总算，苏联和美国是在相互对话，

1342
01:46:18,119 --> 01:46:20,239
instead of at one another.
而不是互相攻击。

1343
01:46:20,439 --> 01:46:21,919
That's just true, man.
咱这次，是真的，伙计。

1344
01:46:34,159 --> 01:46:38,880
Reagan's allies against us included the pope, Thatcher,
里根的那些反对我们的盟友，包括教皇、撒切尔，

1345
01:46:39,319 --> 01:46:43,119
the Iron Lady, and leaders of West Germany and Japan,
那个铁娘子、西德和日本领导人，

1346
01:46:43,399 --> 01:46:44,880
Cole and Nakasone.
科尔和中曾根康弘。

1347
01:46:45,119 --> 01:46:47,119
We stand firmly behind you.
我们坚定地支持你。
（日本首相，中曾根康弘）

1348
01:46:48,399 --> 01:46:54,760
When you speak with Secretary Gorbachev,
you are speaking for us in free word.
当你和戈尔巴乔夫总书记谈话时，你是在用自由的语言，为我们说话。

1349
01:46:55,359 --> 01:46:58,520
Well, we understand that you are surrounded by communists,
我们知道，日本周围，都是共产主义国家，

1350
01:46:59,600 --> 01:47:02,159
and we appreciate you standing with us.
我们很感激，你和我们站在一起。

1351
01:47:02,320 --> 01:47:03,339
Be careful.
小心。

1352
01:47:03,439 --> 01:47:08,319
Remember, communists have no problem with lying to achieve their goals.
记住，共产党人可以毫不犹豫地，为了达到目的，而撒谎。

1353
01:47:09,159 --> 01:47:12,600
They are testing you to see if you will stand firm.
他们在考验你，看你是否坚定。

1354
01:47:12,739 --> 01:47:13,760
Don't worry.
别担心。

1355
01:47:13,960 --> 01:47:16,199
I dealt with these guys back in Hollywood.
我在好莱坞，跟这些人打过交道。

1356
01:47:16,299 --> 01:47:18,580
I even have the scars on my back to prove it.
我背上的伤疤，也证明了这一点。

1357
01:47:18,680 --> 01:47:22,399
And I promise you,we're not going to lose.
我向你保证，我们不会输的。

1358
01:47:24,680 --> 01:47:27,399
In other news, President Reagan has landed in Reykjavik,
其他方面，里根总统抵达冰岛首都雷克雅未克，

1359
01:47:27,499 --> 01:47:32,359
Iceland to continue discussions with Soviet Premier Gorbachev
over nuclear disarmament.
继续与苏联领导人戈尔巴乔夫，就核裁军问题，进行讨论。

1360
01:47:33,319 --> 01:47:35,319
50% across the border reduction.
双方都削减50%的军备。

1361
01:47:36,000 --> 01:47:37,039
All weapons groups.
涵盖全面的武器。

1362
01:47:38,119 --> 01:47:40,399
Tactical, INF, ICBM.
战术导弹，中程导弹，洲际导弹。

1363
01:47:40,960 --> 01:47:44,800
In exchange, suspension of your strategic defense initiative.
作为交换，暂停你方的战略主动防御计划。

1364
01:47:45,220 --> 01:47:46,460
Star Wars.
星球大战计划。

1365
01:47:46,720 --> 01:47:47,800
Some refer to it.
有些人提到了它。

1366
01:47:49,859 --> 01:47:51,300
Counter proposal.
你这是在，讨价还价。

1367
01:47:53,359 --> 01:47:56,960
We share all SDI technology.
我们共享战略主动防御技术。

1368
01:47:58,000 --> 01:47:59,239
We develop it together.
我们一起开发这项技术。

1369
01:47:59,999 --> 01:48:02,200
We'll even pay for it.
我们甚至愿意，为此付钱。

1370
01:48:02,760 --> 01:48:07,279
And we eliminate all ballistic missiles in 10 years.
我们将在10年内，消除所有弹道导弹。

1371
01:48:07,719 --> 01:48:08,879
Together.
我们一起。

1372
01:48:09,159 --> 01:48:13,920
You refuse to share oil drilling technology,and you offer this?
你们拒绝分享石油钻探技术，却提出这个?

1373
01:48:14,199 --> 01:48:18,479
SDI is a completely defensive system.
“战略主动防御”是一个完全的防御系统。

1374
01:48:18,520 --> 01:48:23,800
This is the line, Mr. President.
这是在说台词，总统先生。

1375
01:48:25,119 --> 01:48:33,119
If you walk away, you will have missed the chance of going down
in history as the president who paved the way for nuclear disarmament.
如果你离职时，你将失去作为，为核裁军铺平道路的总统，被载入史册的机会。

1376
01:48:33,680 --> 01:48:37,319
How will you explain this to your free people?
你怎么向你的自由人民解释？

1377
01:48:39,399 --> 01:48:44,239
Mr. President, I'm offering you the biggest win of your presidency.
总统先生，我给你的是，你总统任期内最大的胜利。

1378
01:48:44,960 --> 01:48:46,439
Just drop SDI.
只要放弃，战略主动防御计划。

1379
01:48:46,760 --> 01:48:48,159
Just drop SDI.
只要放弃，战略主动防御计划。

1380
01:49:12,920 --> 01:49:14,520
Yet.
（用俄语说）不。

1381
01:49:18,400 --> 01:49:19,800
Let's go, George.
我们走，乔治。

1382
01:49:27,900 --> 01:49:30,760
You would lose the whole deal over this one thing.
你会因为这事，失去一切的。

1383
01:49:30,960 --> 01:49:32,380
This is a fair offer.
这是一个公平的提议。

1384
01:49:33,260 --> 01:49:34,679
As was mine.
我曾经的（建议）也一样。

1385
01:49:35,099 --> 01:49:37,360
I don't know what more I could have done.
我不知道，我还能做些什么。

1386
01:49:39,619 --> 01:49:41,259
You could have said yes.
你本可以说，“是”的。

1387
01:49:46,239 --> 01:49:51,119
After he walked away from the negotiating table,
we were in a very dark place.
他离开谈判桌后，我们陷入了非常黑暗的境地。

1388
01:49:51,920 --> 01:49:56,199
We knew it was over, unless something extraordinary happened.
我们知道，一切都结束了，除非有什么特别的事发生。

1389
01:50:00,359 --> 01:50:06,479
We've accepted two more shipments of Soviet RPGs
and AK-47s coming out of Cuba, headed for Nicaragua.
我们又截收了两批从古巴运往尼加拉瓜的，苏联火箭弹和AK-47步枪。

1390
01:50:07,300 --> 01:50:09,599
Freedom fighters are holed up in the mountains.
自由战士们躲在山里。

1391
01:50:10,119 --> 01:50:12,560
David and Goliath,but they're making a go of it.
如同大卫和歌利亚作战，但他们成功了。
（副总统，布什）

1392
01:50:13,200 --> 01:50:15,060
Well, I like these guys.
那么，我喜欢这些家伙们。

1393
01:50:15,279 --> 01:50:18,499
They remind me of Washington and the Continental Army.
他们让我想起了乔治.华盛顿和大陆军。

1394
01:50:18,700 --> 01:50:19,980
What do they need?
他们需要什么呢？

1395
01:50:20,279 --> 01:50:21,519
What do they always need?
他们总是需要什么?

1396
01:50:22,159 --> 01:50:23,840
Band-aids, guns, and money.
邦迪创可贴，枪支，还有钱。

1397
01:50:24,900 --> 01:50:26,539
Well, give them what they want.
好吧，给他们想要的。

1398
01:50:27,000 --> 01:50:30,520
Mr. President, we won't have the Congress with us on this one.
总统先生，在这个问题上，我们不会得到国会的支持的。

1399
01:50:40,140 --> 01:50:43,159
And nothing but the truth, for help you God, I do.
我只说真话，上帝保佑，我愿意这么做。
（伊朗门事件听证会）

1400
01:50:43,380 --> 01:50:44,879
Please be served.
请聆讯。

1401
01:50:45,520 --> 01:50:50,199
The American Congress had said no to giving money
to these friends in Nicaragua.
美国国会拒绝向尼加拉瓜的这些朋友们，提供资金。

1402
01:50:51,239 --> 01:50:56,319
And the Crusaders had hostages in the Middle East
and needed to free them.
这些“十字军们”在中东有人质被困，他们需要解救他们。

1403
01:50:56,419 --> 01:51:00,880
But it was American policy never to negotiate with terrorists.
但美国的政策是，绝不与恐怖分子谈判。

1404
01:51:02,119 --> 01:51:04,720
But somewhere, a plan was hatched.
但不知在什么地方，一个计划被酝酿出来了。

1405
01:51:10,640 --> 01:51:14,359
Reagan's Iran-Contra situation comes down to this.
里根的伊朗门事件可以归结为这样。

1406
01:51:14,960 --> 01:51:17,560
What did the president know and when did he know it?
总统知道什么，他什么时候知道的?

1407
01:51:17,660 --> 01:51:20,800
And if you people of the press want any more answers,
如果你们这些媒体想知道更多答案，

1408
01:51:21,119 --> 01:51:22,479
you ask President Reagan.
你们去问里根总统。

1409
01:51:23,319 --> 01:51:25,760
Five decades of his struggle against us,
他和我们抗争了五十年，

1410
01:51:26,199 --> 01:51:30,600
and it came down to whether he could survive a domestic scandal.
现在的问题是，他能否挺过一场国内丑闻。

1411
01:51:31,399 --> 01:51:35,039
In spite of the wildly speculative and false reports,
尽管有很多猜测和虚假的报道，

1412
01:51:35,399 --> 01:51:38,399
we do not negotiate with terrorists.
但我们不会和恐怖分子谈判。

1413
01:51:38,800 --> 01:51:42,499
And we did not trade arms for hostages.
我们也没有，用武器交换人质。

1414
01:51:43,960 --> 01:51:46,600
These accusations are potentially impeachable offenses.
这些指控可能会，遭到弹劾。

1415
01:51:47,079 --> 01:51:50,960
And if true, some observers believe his presidency
could be hanging in the balance.
如果这是真的，一些观察人士认为，他的总统职位可能岌岌可危。

1416
01:51:51,600 --> 01:51:54,619
For WNews4 at the White House, I'm Carl Long.
这里是WNews4在白宫的报道，我是卡尔・朗。

1417
01:52:05,000 --> 01:52:07,439
Bonnie, you have to do something.
亲爱的，你得做点什么。

1418
01:52:08,300 --> 01:52:09,579
Have you seen this?
你看过这个吗?

1419
01:52:10,920 --> 01:52:12,359
Yes, I've seen it.
是的，我看过。

1420
01:52:12,459 --> 01:52:13,940
Are you listening to these people?
你在听这些人说话吗?

1421
01:52:14,920 --> 01:52:16,960
They want nothing more than to see you burn.
他们只想看到，你被烧死。

1422
01:52:17,760 --> 01:52:21,000
You know, they may smile and call you Mr. President,
but they hate you.
他们可能会笑着称你为“总统先生”，但他们讨厌你。

1423
01:52:21,439 --> 01:52:24,359
They hate what you say, what you believe in, who you are.
他们讨厌你说的话，你的信仰，你的为人。

1424
01:52:24,459 --> 01:52:26,279
Honey, I just can't accept that.
亲爱的，我无法接受这些。

1425
01:52:26,379 --> 01:52:28,439
No, no, you never could.
不，不，你永远不会的。

1426
01:52:28,660 --> 01:52:29,760
You're the optimist.
你是乐观主义者。

1427
01:52:29,960 --> 01:52:31,760
You're the one who wants to see the good in people.
你就是那个，愿意看到“人性善”的人。

1428
01:52:32,199 --> 01:52:35,039
But it's my job to see through them and protect you.
但我的职责是，揭穿他们，保护你。

1429
01:52:35,899 --> 01:52:38,519
That's why we're such a good team.
这就是为什么，我们是一个很好的团队。

1430
01:52:41,079 --> 01:52:42,760
Honey, you know Washington.
亲爱的，你了解华盛顿。

1431
01:52:42,860 --> 01:52:43,960
You know the way it works.
你知道，这是怎么回事。

1432
01:52:44,879 --> 01:52:46,600
It's politics.That's all--
这就是政治。这些都是...

1433
01:52:46,700 --> 01:52:47,780
They're talking impeachment.
他们在讨论弹劾。

1434
01:52:48,000 --> 01:52:49,060
Holy impeachment.
要命的弹劾。

1435
01:52:49,359 --> 01:52:51,800
Yes.They want to destroy you.
没错。他们正要毁了你。

1436
01:52:52,239 --> 01:52:55,119
They're putting you on trial, removing you from office.
他们要审判你，把你赶下台。

1437
01:52:55,560 --> 01:52:58,199
This isn't about politics anymore.This is about you.
这已经不是政治问题了。这是关于你个人了。

1438
01:52:59,360 --> 01:53:01,040
Everything is at stake.
一切都危在旦夕。

1439
01:53:01,560 --> 01:53:05,640
One more headline, one more star witness,
one more arrest,and they will do it.
再出一个头条，再出一个明星证人，再逮捕一个人，他们就会这么做。

1440
01:53:06,159 --> 01:53:07,820
I have cooperated with them.
我已经和他们合作了。

1441
01:53:08,239 --> 01:53:10,100
I appointed a special prosecutor.
我任命了一位特别检察官。

1442
01:53:10,359 --> 01:53:13,039
I've turned over every document I have.
我把手头的所有文件，都翻了一遍。

1443
01:53:13,319 --> 01:53:15,000
What would you have me do?
你要我怎么做?

1444
01:53:15,199 --> 01:53:18,560
I want you to fight, or this is all over.
我要你战斗，否则一切都结束了。

1445
01:53:28,039 --> 01:53:31,199
You could always hire someone.
你可以总是雇佣别人。

1446
01:53:33,159 --> 01:53:35,200
Why, you looking for work?
怎么，你在找工作吗?

1447
01:53:35,879 --> 01:53:37,739
I've got a job for you.
我有个工作给你。

1448
01:53:38,400 --> 01:53:43,439
Back in Washington,
you're the president, you could always order me back there.
-回华盛顿去。  -你是总统，你随时可以，命令我回去。

1449
01:53:45,220 --> 01:53:47,300
Are they going to impeach me, Bill?
他们会弹劾我吗，比尔?

1450
01:53:48,039 --> 01:53:50,479
Yeah, let's move in that direction, sir.
对，我们朝那个方向走，先生。

1451
01:53:53,460 --> 01:53:55,319
Mr. President, you're my friend.
总统先生，你是我的朋友。

1452
01:53:55,560 --> 01:53:56,840
I can only speak to you straight.
我只能对你直言不讳。

1453
01:53:57,920 --> 01:54:02,840
Some laws got broken for sure,
whether you broke them or somebody else did.
有些法律是肯定会被违反的，不管你违反了它们，还是别人违反了它们。

1454
01:54:03,640 --> 01:54:06,640
So now you're clamming up and lawyering up.
所以，现在你三缄其口，还请了律师。

1455
01:54:06,919 --> 01:54:08,780
It's a wrong move.
这招棋，你走错了。

1456
01:54:09,039 --> 01:54:11,119
Confuses everybody,even the ones that love you.
让所有人困惑，即使是爱你的人。

1457
01:54:12,140 --> 01:54:15,179
People are thinking that maybe you're losing it.
-大家都在想，也许你...  -理亏词穷。

1458
01:54:15,439 --> 01:54:15,640
Yeah.
是的。

1459
01:54:16,999 --> 01:54:18,020
I've heard it.
我听说了。

1460
01:54:22,680 --> 01:54:24,199
What do you think I should do, Judge?
你觉得我该怎么做，法官大人？

1461
01:54:25,160 --> 01:54:26,239
What you do best?
什么是你最擅长的？

1462
01:54:26,999 --> 01:54:28,460
Tell them the truth?
告诉他们真相。

1463
01:54:51,760 --> 01:54:56,560
A few months ago, I told the American people
that I did not trade arms for hostages.
几个月前，我告诉美国人民，我不会用武器交换人质。

1464
01:54:57,239 --> 01:55:01,079
My heart and my best intentions still tell me that's true.
我的内心和我最善良的意愿，仍然告诉我，这是真的。

1465
01:55:01,680 --> 01:55:05,159
But the facts and the evidence tell me it is not.
但事实和证据告诉我，事实并非如此。

1466
01:55:05,800 --> 01:55:08,920
Now, what should happen when you make a mistake is this.
现在，当你犯错误的时候，应该是这样的。

1467
01:55:09,380 --> 01:55:12,600
You take your knocks,you put things in perspective,
哪里跌倒，就在哪里爬起来，正确看待问题，

1468
01:55:13,079 --> 01:55:16,399
you pull your energies together, you make changes,
集中精力，做出改变，

1469
01:55:16,959 --> 01:55:18,439
and you go forward.
然后继续前进。

1470
01:55:19,520 --> 01:55:22,520
Americans, you do them wrong, you'll pay for it.
对于美国人民，如果你错看了他们，你会付出代价的。

1471
01:55:23,159 --> 01:55:26,319
You looked them in the eye, that made you make a mistake.
如果你光看着他们的眼睛，这让会你犯错误的。

1472
01:55:27,359 --> 01:55:29,079
They forgive you every time.
他们每次都原谅你。

1473
01:55:44,720 --> 01:55:46,619
He was president.
他当时是总统。

1474
01:55:46,920 --> 01:55:47,800
He had to know.
他必须知道这点。

1475
01:55:50,079 --> 01:55:53,539
He was still the lifeguard.
他还是当年的那个救生员。

1476
01:55:53,780 --> 01:55:56,200
He was going to get his people home.
他必须把他的人质，带回家。

1477
01:55:58,000 --> 01:56:00,000
英国，伦敦

1478
01:56:00,200 --> 01:56:03,960
I am not pleased with you, Ron.Let's just get that said right up front.
我对你这样做不满意，罗恩。我们先把这个说出来。

1479
01:56:05,319 --> 01:56:07,720
Well, I can't imagine how I've upset you, Margaret.
我无法想象，我让你有多难过，玛格丽特。

1480
01:56:07,820 --> 01:56:09,680
Are we going to go over a grenade again?
我们还要再经历一次，出兵格林纳达吗?

1481
01:56:10,159 --> 01:56:14,319
Well, you're certainly not walking away
from what happened at Reykjavik.
你肯定还没有从雷克雅未克的事情中脱身。

1482
01:56:14,479 --> 01:56:15,519
No.
不是的。

1483
01:56:15,640 --> 01:56:17,139
Looks like you're picking a fight.
看起来,你是在选择一场战斗。

1484
01:56:17,600 --> 01:56:19,960
No, but I'm not afraid of one.
没有，但我不怕战斗。

1485
01:56:20,720 --> 01:56:26,079
Perhaps that is why Mitterrand calls you a dangerous cowboy.
也许,这就是密特朗称你为"危险牛仔"的原因。

1486
01:56:27,720 --> 01:56:32,000
Well, at least I had Margaret Thatcher on my side.
至少,还有玛格丽特・撒切尔站在我这边。

1487
01:56:37,700 --> 01:56:38,960
He wants to say it.
他想说出来。

1488
01:56:39,160 --> 01:56:40,199
He does, but we'll never get it past Schultz.
是的，但舒尔茨是不会同意的。

1489
01:56:40,359 --> 01:56:42,479
I mean, it's the one thing they don't want him talking about.
我是说，这是唯一，他们不想让他触及的事情。

1490
01:56:42,579 --> 01:56:44,460
My family in Germany is talking about it.
我在德国的家人，正在谈论这件事。

1491
01:56:44,560 --> 01:56:45,680
Everybody is talking about it.
每个人都在谈论它。

1492
01:56:45,780 --> 01:56:46,820
He needs to talk about it.
他需要把它说出来.

1493
01:56:47,000 --> 01:56:49,800
He's going to Camp David,then he's back here for a day,
then he's going to Europe.
他要去戴维营，然后在这里待一天，然后去欧洲。

1494
01:56:49,960 --> 01:56:52,800
We have one shot to have him say this.
我们只有一次机会，让他这么说。

1495
01:56:53,099 --> 01:56:55,180
It's now or never.
要么现在，要么永远别说。

1496
01:57:08,000 --> 01:57:10,560
Hey, give me this.I'll take it.Thank you.
嘿,把这个给我。我来拿着。谢谢你。

1497
01:57:11,999 --> 01:57:14,199
Mr. President, some light reading.
总统先生，这是需要你念的“台词本”。
（联邦德国，西柏林）

1498
01:57:26,220 --> 01:57:27,719
Hello, fellas.
你们好，小伙子们。

1499
01:57:27,999 --> 01:57:29,480
Good day to fly.
今天是飞行的好日子。

1500
01:57:29,700 --> 01:57:30,960
No barrel rules.
不用借助外力。

1501
01:58:10,579 --> 01:58:12,600
Well, I think that's a first lady question.
我觉得，这是该由第一夫人，回答的问题。

1502
01:58:13,039 --> 01:58:15,120
Why would you do this to Gorbachev?
你为什么要对戈尔巴乔夫，做这些？

1503
01:58:15,799 --> 01:58:18,200
You know how long it's taken us to get to this.
你知道，我们花了多长时间，才走到这一步。

1504
01:58:18,480 --> 01:58:21,520
They're at the table.They're ready to make a deal.
And you want to embarrass him?
他们在桌子旁。他们准备好做交易了。而你想让他难堪吗?

1505
01:58:22,119 --> 01:58:24,399
Gorbachev's the first friend we've had over there in 70 years.
戈尔巴乔夫是我们70年来，在那里的第一个朋友。

1506
01:58:25,859 --> 01:58:27,499
You can't say this.
你不能说这些话。

1507
01:58:27,720 --> 01:58:29,379
I'm begging you to listen to me.
我求你听我说。

1508
01:58:29,879 --> 01:58:32,560
I stood by you with STI when it was ridiculed.
当人们嘲笑你应对性传播疾病时，我站在你一边。

1509
01:58:33,680 --> 01:58:35,039
I supported you with a contrast.
当武器换人质时，我支持你。

1510
01:58:35,640 --> 01:58:37,880
I even walked out a Reykjavik with egg on my face.
当我从雷克雅为克走出来时，我还为你挨了一颗鸡蛋，砸我脸上。

1511
01:58:38,480 --> 01:58:40,579
But this goes too far.
但你这么做，太过分了。

1512
01:58:41,220 --> 01:58:43,479
This is worse than evil, Empire.
这比你称他们为邪恶帝国，还糟糕。

1513
01:58:43,720 --> 01:58:46,379
You've got to blow up, Geneva.You'll blow up eight years of diplomacy.
在日内瓦，你已经毁了一次。这次，你要毁了八年来的外交努力。

1514
01:58:46,760 --> 01:58:49,360
It'll be right back where we started from or worse.
它会回到原点，甚至更糟。

1515
01:58:52,380 --> 01:58:54,459
Clarity is power.
透明度，就是力量。

1516
01:58:54,719 --> 01:58:58,120
You know, a very great man once said that to me.
一个非常伟大的人，曾经对我说过这句话。

1517
01:58:59,200 --> 01:59:01,240
What are we here for, George?
我们来这里，是干什么的？乔治。

1518
01:59:02,279 --> 01:59:04,720
But to win.
除了取胜，还是取胜。

1519
01:59:09,360 --> 01:59:12,360
（1987年，联邦德国，西柏林）

1520
01:59:12,560 --> 01:59:21,560
Behind me stands a wall,part of a vast system of barriers
that divide the entire continent of Europe.
在我身后矗立着一堵墙，这是将整个欧洲大陆，分隔开来的巨大障碍系统的一部分。

1521
01:59:22,399 --> 01:59:33,399
A gash, a barbed wire concrete, dogs, and guard towers,
imposing the will of a totalitarian state.
带铁丝网的混凝土筑起的一道伤口，警犬和炮楼，彰显着极权主义国家的意志。

1522
01:59:34,600 --> 01:59:43,840
As long as this gate is closed and this scar is permitted to stand,
there is a question of freedom for all mankind.
只要这扇门还关着，这道伤疤就还存在，全人类对自由的疑问，就还存在。

1523
01:59:52,560 --> 01:59:55,920
The totalitarian world produces backwardness
极权主义世界之所以产生了落后，

1524
01:59:56,760 --> 01:59:59,479
because it does such violence to the spirit,
是因为它对人类的精神世界，造成如此的暴力，

1525
02:00:00,039 --> 02:00:04,039
affording the human impulse to create, to enjoy,
正是那个精神世界，给了人类创造，享受，甚至是，

1526
02:00:04,320 --> 02:00:06,220
even to worship.
崇拜的冲动。

1527
02:00:06,720 --> 02:00:09,600
Here in Berlin, like the city itself,
在柏林的这里，就像这座城市本身一样，

1528
02:00:10,880 --> 02:00:15,840
symbols of love, symbols of worship, cannot be suppressed.
是爱的象征，是崇拜的象征，不可能被压抑。

1529
02:00:16,199 --> 02:00:17,960
[CHEERING]
[欢呼声]

1530
02:00:24,279 --> 02:00:30,920
There is one sign that the Soviets could make that would
unmistakably and dramatically
有一件事，是苏联人可以做的，那就是明确无误地、大张旗鼓地

1531
02:00:31,600 --> 02:00:34,479
advance the cause of freedom and peace.
推进自由与和平事业。

1532
02:00:35,840 --> 02:00:39,720
General Secretary Gorbachev, if you seek peace,
戈尔巴乔夫总书记，如果你寻求和平，

1533
02:00:40,439 --> 02:00:45,920
if you seek liberalization and change, come here to this gate.
如果你寻求自由化和变革，请到这扇门前来。

1534
02:00:46,020 --> 02:00:48,159
[CHEERING]
[欢呼声]

1535
02:00:48,600 --> 02:00:52,439
Mr. Gorbachev, open this gate.
戈尔巴乔夫先生，打开这扇门。

1536
02:00:53,779 --> 02:00:55,000
Is he going to save?
他这不是说出了吗？

1537
02:01:01,399 --> 02:01:05,840
Mr. Gorbachev, tear down this wall.
戈尔巴乔夫先生，推倒这堵墙吧！

1538
02:01:11,360 --> 02:01:12,599
[CHEERING]
[欢呼声]

1539
02:01:26,279 --> 02:01:28,760
Well done, cowboy man.
干的漂亮，我的牛仔。

1540
02:02:07,439 --> 02:02:11,640
In the chess game of the Cold War, it was checkmate.
在冷战的棋局中，它是将死对手的一招棋。

1541
02:02:15,960 --> 02:02:19,520
两年后的1989年

1542
02:02:20,700 --> 02:02:24,119
The unimaginable is happening right now in Berlin.
难以想象的事情，正在柏林发生。

1543
02:02:25,079 --> 02:02:29,760
Shocking developments overnight as East Germany
announced its citizens can travel freely to West Germany.
一夜之间发生了令人震惊的事情，东德政府宣布，其公民可以自由前往西德。

1544
02:02:30,520 --> 02:02:34,800
What no one thought could happen is happening right now.
没人想到会发生的事情，现在正在发生。

1545
02:03:03,640 --> 02:03:06,079
Within hours, the city erupted in celebration
就在几个小时之内。在这座城市爆发出欢庆，

1546
02:03:06,319 --> 02:03:11,039
as East and West Germans took hammers to the wall that
had separated them for 30 years.
东德人和西德人用铁锤，砸开分隔了他们30年的柏林墙。

1547
02:03:21,880 --> 02:03:26,680
Two years after the world fell, the Soviet Union was no more.
在我们的世界崩溃两年后，苏联不复存在。

1548
02:03:30,540 --> 02:03:32,599
I knew he was the one.
我知道，他就是那个人。

1549
02:03:34,359 --> 02:03:37,079
He was the one who would bring us down,
是他，把我们搞垮的，

1550
02:03:37,880 --> 02:03:41,359
not with missiles or guns or even politics,
不是用导弹，不是用枪，也不是用政治，

1551
02:03:41,879 --> 02:03:43,319
something much greater.
而是用更强大的东西。

1552
02:03:50,199 --> 02:03:56,000
People will not give their lives for power or a state or even ideology.
人们不会为权力、为国家，甚至为了意识形态，而付出生命。

1553
02:03:57,960 --> 02:04:00,560
People give their lives for one another,
人们为彼此献出生命，

1554
02:04:02,119 --> 02:04:05,760
for the freedom to live those lives as they choose,and for God.
为了自由选择自己的生活，也为了上帝。

1555
02:04:05,960 --> 02:04:09,560
《德尔的印刷工》讲一个男孩迪尔.福克纳沦落到中西部的小镇博伊德，
生活窘困时，被一个印刷商雇佣，成为了一名虔诚的基督徒，通过努力，
有成为能够拯救博伊德的牧师，后又去了华盛顿，踏上政坛了...

1556
02:04:09,779 --> 02:04:11,779
We took that away.
我们接受了那套方式。

1557
02:04:14,279 --> 02:04:18,319
The crusader would give it back to them.
那个十字军把它还给了他们。

1558
02:04:29,520 --> 02:04:32,319
And that is the answer to your question.
这就是你问题的答案。

1559
02:04:36,179 --> 02:04:38,399
Thank you, Mr. Petrovich.
谢谢你，彼得罗维奇先生。

1560
02:04:54,080 --> 02:04:55,359
Take it.
拿去吧。

1561
02:05:01,340 --> 02:05:02,359
Thank you.
谢谢你。

1562
02:05:04,440 --> 02:05:05,479
Good night.
晚安。

1563
02:05:36,079 --> 02:05:37,479
What's going on there, Mr. President?
发生什么事了，总统先生?

1564
02:05:37,520 --> 02:05:40,640
[MUSIC PLAYING]

1565
02:05:40,800 --> 02:05:42,399
This means something to me.
这对我来说很重要。

1566
02:05:44,920 --> 02:05:48,399
I know what you're saying,John, but I'm not going to do it.
我知道你在说什么，约翰，但我不会这么做的。

1567
02:05:49,279 --> 02:05:51,640
Ma'am, we need you to tell him we can't do this anymore.
女士，我们需要你告诉他，我们不能再这样下去了。

1568
02:05:52,039 --> 02:05:54,640
I can't.I can't.I can't do it.
我不能。我不能。我不能这么做。

1569
02:05:56,100 --> 02:05:57,600
He got lost yesterday.
他昨天迷路了。

1570
02:05:58,660 --> 02:06:00,679
Couldn't find him for half an hour.
半个小时，都找不到他。

1571
02:06:01,340 --> 02:06:04,220
Horses know when a rider doesn't know what he's doing, OK?
马匹知道，骑手不知道自己在做什么，对吗?

1572
02:06:05,380 --> 02:06:07,020
He's going to get thrown again.
他又要被甩出去了一次。

1573
02:06:08,099 --> 02:06:11,160
I can't tell him that he can't ride anymore.
我不能告诉他，他不能再骑马了。

1574
02:06:13,460 --> 02:06:15,479
He loves it too much.
他太喜欢骑马了。

1575
02:06:16,459 --> 02:06:17,579
Please.
求你了。

1576
02:06:22,119 --> 02:06:23,119
OK.
好吧。

1577
02:06:28,719 --> 02:06:31,160
He loves you more, ma'am.
他更喜欢你，夫人。

1578
02:06:50,340 --> 02:06:51,600
Mr. President?
总统先生？

1579
02:06:54,440 --> 02:06:55,859
What is it, John?
约翰去哪儿了？

1580
02:06:59,239 --> 02:07:06,039
You know, I don't think we're having as much fun riding as we used to.
你知道吗，我觉得我们不像以前，骑得那么开心了。

1581
02:07:06,239 --> 02:07:09,600
Oh, the agent on Mrs. Reagan, she is--
哦，负责保卫里根夫人的特勤局侍卫，她在...

1582
02:07:09,700 --> 02:07:11,539
What do you want, John?
你想要说什么，约翰?

1583
02:07:15,960 --> 02:07:20,079
Mr. President, I don't--I don't think we should ride anymore.
总统先生，我觉得...我们不该再骑马了。

1584
02:07:22,920 --> 02:07:23,960
Oh.
哦。

1585
02:07:27,439 --> 02:07:30,239
[SIGH]
[叹气声]

1586
02:07:52,740 --> 02:07:53,760
One more ride.
再骑一次。

1587
02:07:57,560 --> 02:07:59,200
Yes, sir, Mr. President.
是的，先生，总统先生。

1588
02:08:03,399 --> 02:08:06,760
[MUSIC PLAYING]

1589
02:08:33,399 --> 02:08:43,520
[约翰.丹佛的《乡间路带我回家》前奏响起]

1590
02:08:45,819 --> 02:08:49,079
My fellow Americans, I have recently
我的美国同胞们，我最近被告知，

1591
02:08:49,239 --> 02:08:54,880
been told that I am one of the millions of Americans who
will be afflicted with Alzheimer's disease.
我是数百万，遭受阿尔茨海默病折磨的美国人之一。

1592
02:08:56,439 --> 02:08:58,600
At the moment, I feel just fine.
现在，我感觉很好。

1593
02:08:59,960 --> 02:09:05,760
I intend to live the remainder of the years God gives me,
doing the things I have always done.
我打算在上帝赐予我的余生中，做我一直在做的事情。

1594
02:09:06,920 --> 02:09:10,439
Unfortunately, as Alzheimer's disease progresses,
不幸的是，随着阿尔茨海默病的发展，

1595
02:09:11,159 --> 02:09:13,600
the family often bears a heavy burden.
家人往往承受着沉重的负担。

1596
02:09:14,560 --> 02:09:20,000
I only wish there was some way I could spare Nancy
from this painful experience.
我只希望有什么办法，能让南希免于这种痛苦的经历。

1597
02:09:21,720 --> 02:09:25,920
I will continue to share life's journey
 with my beloved Nancy and my family.
我将继续与我心爱的南希，和我的家人，分享人生的旅程。

1598
02:09:27,239 --> 02:09:32,880
I plan to enjoy the great outdoors
and stay in touch with my friends and supporters.
我打算好好享受户外活动，并与我的朋友和支持者，保持联系。

1599
02:09:34,600 --> 02:09:42,119
When the time comes, I am confident that with your help,
she will face it with faith and courage.
到时候，我相信在你们的帮助下，她会满怀信心和勇气面对不幸。

1600
02:09:45,079 --> 02:09:50,079
All my memories gather round her.
我所有的记忆，都围绕着她。

1601
02:09:51,359 --> 02:09:56,880
Minor's lady, stranger to blue waters.
一个娇小的女人，对蓝色的海水充满陌生。

1602
02:09:59,199 --> 02:10:07,560
Dark and dusty, painted on the sky, misty taste of moonshine,
黑暗和尘土，涂抹在天空，弥漫着朦胧的月光的味道，

1603
02:10:07,880 --> 02:10:18,119
teardrop in my eye,country roads take me home to the place
泪水夺眶而出，乡间道路带我回家，回到那个

1604
02:10:19,439 --> 02:10:30,960
I belong, West Virginia, mountain mama, take me home,
我属于这里的地方，西弗吉尼亚，群山母亲，带我回家，

1605
02:10:32,159 --> 02:10:42,960
country roads, country roads take me home to the place
乡间道路，乡间道路带我回家，回到那

1606
02:10:44,019 --> 02:10:46,319
I belong.
我属于的地方。

1607
02:10:48,159 --> 02:10:51,880
In closing, let me thank you, the American people,
最后，让我感谢你们，美国人民，

1608
02:10:52,359 --> 02:10:57,039
for giving me the great honor of allowing me to serve
 as your president.
感谢你们给予我极大的荣誉，允许我担任你们的总统。

1609
02:10:58,159 --> 02:11:01,760
When the Lord calls me home, whenever that may be,
当上帝召唤我回家时，无论何时，

1610
02:11:02,640 --> 02:11:08,800
I will leave with the greatest love for this country of ours
 and eternal optimism for its future.
我都将带着对我们国家最大的爱，和对未来永远的乐观，离开这个世界。

1611
02:11:09,800 --> 02:11:13,840
I now begin the journey that will lead me into the sunset of my life.
我现在开始了一段旅程，它将把我带入人生的黄昏。

1612
02:11:14,399 --> 02:11:19,520
I know that for America, there will always be a bright new dawn ahead.
我知道，对于美国来说，前方总会有一个光明的新黎明。

1613
02:11:20,560 --> 02:11:21,560
Thank you, my friends.
谢谢你们，我的朋友们。

1614
02:11:22,820 --> 02:11:25,800
May God always bless you.
愿上帝永远保佑你们。

1615
02:11:26,200 --> 02:11:50,000
翻译：hardstick  校订：hardstick  时间轴：hardstick

1616
02:11:26,239 --> 02:11:29,640
Sincerely, Ronald Reagan.
真诚的罗纳德・里根。


